title: banana pudding
directions: Mix and cook in double boiler until thick.
Put vanilla wafers and bananas in bowl; pour mixture over wafers and bananas.
Use egg white to make topping.
Use mixer until thick.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and teaspoon vanilla.
Put on top.
Cook in oven until brown on top.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine egg with water.
Sprinkle over flour mixture.
Add vinegar and stir mixture forming a ball.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill for at least 1 hour or until ready to use.
Yield:
pastry for about 1 1/2 dozen (5-inch) pies.

title: summertime strawberry cooler
directions: Puree 2 cups strawberries in blender.
Add water, sugar, lemon juice, lemon rind and ginger ale.
Blend well.
Chill and pour into cups.
Slice remaining berries and use for garnish.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Roll out 2/3 of the pastry 1/8-inch thick. Fit into 9-inch pie pan.
Trim pastry, leaving 1 edge.
Roll remaining pastry 1/8-inch thick into rectangle, about 10 x 6-inch; cut into 12 strips, 1/2-inch wide.
Melt butter over low heat. Blend in flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in chicken broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Place 7 strips of pastry across filling; arrange remaining strips crisscross fashion to make a lattice-type top.
Trim; turn edge of bottom crust over strips. Seal and flute.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry cheese salad
directions: Crush berries well, mix with sugar and lemon juice.
Mix small portion at a time with cream cheese until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into refrigerator trays and freeze until firm.
Serve in slices on lettuce leaf.
May be used with crushed pineapple, drained also, or with mashed bananas in place of strawberries.
Omit lemon juice.

title: new orleans style caesar salad
directions: With a whisk, mix together the garlic and onion.
Add mustard (approximately 2 tablespoons) to your own taste.
Add vegetable oil and red wine vinegar in equal amounts.
Add dash of salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Toss with romaine lettuce, Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: vi's very scrumptious vegetarian spaghetti sauce
directions: Pour cook one healthy glass of Burgundy (the cook needs something to get through all that chopping!).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserving 1/2 cup cheese and the almonds.
Put in casserole; top with cheese and almonds
and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: In large heavy skillet, put enough oil to cover bottom.
Saute onions and garlic until limp and golden.
Add shrimp and water. Heat to simmer and cook for 10 minutes.
Wash rice and add to shrimp mixture with green onions, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly and cook rapidly until most water is gone and rice begins to puff. Lower heat, cover and cook approximately 20 minutes or until rice is cooked and shrimp are tender but firm.
Serves 6.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.
Don't overcook.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with half of the pastry.
Roll out remainder for top crust.
Combine remaining ingredients and fill shell.
Top with rolled out pastry and crimp edges to seal.
Cut four 1-inch slits in top crust to vent.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: celery casserole
directions: Put celery in boiling, salted water and cook 8 minutes; drain. Layer celery, water chestnuts, pimiento and chicken soup in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with sliced almonds; crumble Ritz crackers lightly over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown meat slowly along with green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in water, tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
In a 2-quart casserole, mix together cooked noodles, meat sauce and Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes a very delicious meal.

title: baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cut chicken into 8 pieces and wash very well.
Lay in baking pan, skin side up.
Melt margarine and brush chicken with it.
Sprinkle with onion powder.
Mix seasoned salt, flour and pepper together and sprinkle over chicken.
Cook in oven for 45 minutes.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dates, water and 1/2 cup sugar in saucepan.
Cook until thick (2 to 3 minutes) stirring constantly.
Cool.
Thoroughly cream butter and sugars; add egg and beat well; add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; stir until smooth.
Divide dough in half; roll one part on well-floured surface until 1/4 inch thick.
Combine date mixture and nuts; spread half of filling evenly over dough.
Roll like a jelly roll; wrap in waxed paper with open edge of roll on bottom. Repeat with remaining dough and filling.
Chill rolls until firm. Cut in 1/4 inch slices.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: apple and cherry upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix sugar with melted oleo.
Add can of apple pie filling; spread evenly.
On top of apples, add the cherry pie filling.
Make cake according to directions on box.
Pour over the other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool, then turn out on tray.
Serve with whipped cream (optional).

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Add oil and milk; mix well.
Add sugar, a little at a time, then add flour, a little at a time.
Add vanilla; fold in berries.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick lasagna(power level: high, 100%; low, 30%)
directions: Place ground beef in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High (100%) for 6 to 8 minutes or until pink in center.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons grease.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Hull berries; set aside.
Combine pie filling mix, sour cream, milk, rind and 2 cups whipped topping.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 1 minute.
Spoon half into crust.
Arrange berries; press them down into filling.
Top with remaining filling.
Freeze for 1 hour or chill for 3 hours in refrigerator.

title: tomato-onion salad with herbs
directions: Combine onion and ice water to cover in bowl.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Soaking the onions will remove its strong bitter flavor. Drain onions until dry.
Arrange on serving platter with tomatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Whisk together vinegar, parsley, thyme, oregano and 1/4 teaspoon salt in bowl.
Add oil gradually until well blended.
Drizzle dressing over onions and tomatoes. Makes 8 servings.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk and bring to a boil. Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Mix and spoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers as directed on package.
Cool.
Put 1 layer in punch bowl, pressing down.
Pour on 1 package prepared pudding mix.
Let cool until set, then add half of coconut, pecans, strawberries, Marshmallow Creme, pineapple, peaches, fruit cocktail, oranges, banana and whipped topping.
Add second cake; layer pudding, coconut, nuts, Marshmallow Creme and fruit.
Finish with remaining whipped topping.
Decorate with whole strawberries and peaches.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook sugar and 1 cup water to make a thin syrup.
Add gelatin which has been soaked in 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into an 8 cup mold and chill.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: 3 cheese bake
directions: Simple; boil noodles and drain.
Mix in all cheeses.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Any 3 cheeses can be used for this dish and kids love it.
(A variation of macaroni & cheese.)

title: chinese spaghetti
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and place on oiled cookie sheet.
Place in oven at 350° and cook until slightly brown.
Brown meat; add garlic salt and soy sauce.
Put this aside, leaving oil in your large pan.
Brown onion and pepper in remaining oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add meat back in and adjust spices to taste.
Pour sauce over hot noodles and serve.

title: raisin whole wheat bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Place bread cubes in 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with raisins. Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in egg and vanilla. Heat milk; slowly stir into egg mixture. Pour over bread. Bake until tip of knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 40 minutes. Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: lasagne(serves 6)
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cook the onions and garlic in butter and olive oil.
When limp, but not brown, add the beef and cook, stirring frequently until well done.
Add the wine; cover tightly and steam for 5 minutes.
Add the basil, tomato paste, puree and juice.
Add the green pepper, celery, pepper and nutmeg and cook for 10 minutes.
Boil lasagne in water for 15 minutes.
Plunge in cold water for ease in handling, then drain.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, cut into small cubes and boil for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain and add 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix in beaten egg and 1/2 cup seasoned bread crumbs (Pepperidge Farm dressing mix), finely chopped onion and salt, pepper and seasoning salt to taste.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: hot dog hash
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Dice hot dogs and chop onion.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet.
Add potatoes and onion.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Add hot dogs and cook for 10 minutes until brown.
Add mustard, mix well.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chewy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine cake mix, eggs and melted butter in large bowl. Stir until thoroughly blended (mixture will be stiff). Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Press mixture evenly in pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Do not overbake. Cool. Cut into squares and dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: chili
directions: Thoroughly brown and drain hamburger and rinse with hot water before adding other ingredients.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Rinse beans before adding to other ingredients.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over cake top after removing from oven.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place milk and chocolate over low heat, stirring, until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook gently to 236°, stirring from bottom occasionally. Remove from heat.
Add butter; cool without stirring to lukewarm. Add vanilla.
Beat until thick and no longer glossy.
Stir in nuts.
Turn onto waxed paper and shape into 12-inch roll; chill and slice.
May be spread in buttered pan and cut into squares. Yield:
1 1/4 pounds.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Mix soda with 1 tablespoon water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in flour and salt. Blend well.
Add oatmeal and raisins (and nuts, if desired). Spoon out by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Heat the cooking oil in electric frypan to 350°.
Saute the onion until soft and transparent but not brown.
Add beef cubes and brown.
Add stock, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cover, reduce heat to 250° and simmer 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and tomato juice.
Simmer 30 minutes longer or until beef is tender and vegetables are cooked.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions.
Serve goulash over noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients the night before.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gisela's apple cake
directions: Combine last 7 ingredients in a bowl and microwave for 4 minutes.
Arrange on top of cake mixture from refrigerator in a pretty design.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the pineapple juice.
Chill until thick, but not completely set.
Add blueberries and pecans.
Reserve 1/2 cup Jell-O and mix with whipped topping.
Return Jell-O mixture and whipped topping mixture to refrigerator.
Chill until completely set.
When ready to serve, spread topping mixture over Jell-O mixture and cut into squares.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain and return to pan.
Add honey and remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until butter and sugar melt.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 2 minutes after each.
Add flour alternately with milk; blend in flavoring and coconut until well mixed.
Pour in tube pan; bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours (or until done).
Do not preheat oven.

title: cheese cake
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with crushed graham crackers, mixed with the melted oleo.
Combine the water, jello and sugar; let cool 20 minutes.
Add the cream cheese.
Whip the Milnot until like whipped cream; add to cream cheese mixture.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: This quickie frozen salad is popular for a party luncheon menu.
Drain fruit cocktail and combine it with a creamy smooth dressing of cream cheese, cream or sour cream and lemon juice. Turn into a refrigerator tray and freeze until firm.
Package in moisture-proof container.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and mold.
Place in slow cooker with large can tomatoes or tomato sauce.

title: easy lo-fat banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk as indicated on pudding box in a large bowl. Blend in vanilla wafers and cut up bananas or line Pyrex dish with bananas and vanilla wafers and pour pudding on top.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes and then top with lo-fat Cool Whip, if desired.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Line muffin pan with 12 paper baking cups. In a medium bowl combine cereal, flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt. In a large bowl combine applesauce, honey, oil, egg and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients and mix well. Add apples. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 9 ingredients; mix well.
Beat in sweet potatoes.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 40 to 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: mexi - spaghetti
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, soup and beans. Simmer.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut cooked chicken breasts into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas.
Add the chicken broth; stir until thickened.
Add sour cream & chilies; do not boil.
Add additional chicken broth to moisten the mixture.
Put approx. 1 Tbsp. mixture in soft tortillas.
Fold; pour 1/2 of the sauce (see below) in dish that has been sprayed with Pam; then place the filled tortillas, then the rest of the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 min. Top with cheese.
Turn oven off for cheese to melt.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: In pan, mix gelatin and water; let stand 5 minutes to soften. Heat just until it dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Stir in undrained berries.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl, over cake pieces; mix gently.
Pour into an ungreased 8-inch dish. Chill until firm.

title: scallops
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup mushroom juice.
Saute onions and mushrooms in margarine.
Add juice, milk, flour and scallops to onion and mushrooms in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and paprika. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry streusel cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and add blueberries.
Spread in 8-inch greased pan.
Top with topping.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Put steak in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour your soup, water, mushrooms and soup mix over top.
Cook at 375° for 2 hours.
Turn over halfway through.
Serve over top of rice.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add soup and water, 1/3 Cheez Whiz and chestnuts.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with the remaining Cheez Whiz which has been softened.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix well the Bisquick, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla with a spoon. Add pecans, mixing well. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cake will usually sink in the middle.

title: poultry filling
directions: Bring to boil the water, onion, butter, celery, poultry seasoning, pepper, salt, mustard and parsley.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over bread cubes.
Stuff meat.
Bake until meat is cooked.

title: granny liz's potato rolls
directions: Peel potato and cut it up.
Boil in 5 cups of water.
Put heaping tablespoonful of shortening in bowl and add 1 cup potato water.
In separate bowl, mash potato and add 1 cup potato water. Combine contents of both bowls and add salt, sugar, egg and milk; stir.
Combine 2 cups flour with yeast.
Add to liquid and mix well.
Add 5 cups flour and knead well.
Let rise in greased bowl 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and make rolls.
Let rolls rise 1 hour, then bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix self-rising flour, sugar and milk.
Sprinkle over melted butter and then your peaches on fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: boiled shrimp in beer
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and bring back to a vigorous boil for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove pan from heat and let cool. Strain and then discard all seasonings.
Chill shrimp and serve with cocktail sauce.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash brown patties and crumble them in 9 x 13-inch pan, about 3/4 to 1-inch deep.
Brown the sausage and spread over the hash browns.
Grate or shred the cheese and spread over sausage.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over cheese layer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 400° until bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Arrange 6 slices on bottom of greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover bread with half the cheese slices; repeat layers.
Combine eggs and remaining ingredients; pour over bread and cheese.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix jello
with 1 cup hot water.
Add berries and break apart with
fork.
Add 1 cup cold water.	When thick, add cake broken in small
pieces and 1/2 whipped Dream Whip.	Mix well and pour
in tube pan.
Let this get solid, turn out on plate. Refrigerate
and be sure it's firm.	Spread remainder of Dream Whip	overall.
Can be used with pineapple and coconut sprinkled on top.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat in large saucepan. Take from heat; add sugar, milk and salt.
Beat until smooth. Stir in vanilla.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into ball (1 large or 2 small).
Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: coffee punch
directions: Boil water with cinnamon stick.
Mix coffee and sugar with water and cinnamon stick.
Cool.
Refrigerate.
When well chilled, add milk.
Punch can be made a day in advance.

title: gingerbread bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda in a bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is the consistency of cornmeal.
Stir in the buttermilk.
Dough needs to be pliable and easy to roll.
If dough is too sticky, add a little flour at a time.
Roll out dough on a floured surface and knead lightly.
Cut biscuits and place on a buttered pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: light touch dessert
directions: Blend all together.
Serve over lettuce leaves for salad.

title: bourbon balls(these do not require baking.)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and shape into balls the size of an English walnut. Roll
in confectioners sugar.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll in ground pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix fruit, flour, sugar and butter well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with another pie shell.
Put holes in top of pie with a fork.
Put several slices of butter on top of pie. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cream chicken and wild rice soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients including contents of seasoning packet from rice mix; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium to high heat.
Reduce heat to medium; cook 10 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Beat shortening until creamy; add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Add bananas, oatmeal and nuts.
Mix together thoroughly. Add flour mixture.
Blend.
Drop on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from sheet at once.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: the best pork barbecue(for slow cooker)
directions: Remove meat from bone; cut in chunks and place in slow cooker. (Discard skin, fat and bone.)
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil in a small saucepan or in cup in microwave oven. Pour over meat.
Stir thoroughly and cover.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve on hamburger buns with cole slaw.

title: hamburger au gratin
directions: Fry ground chuck until brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; stir frequently.
Reduce heat to simmer, stirring occasionally until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pamper yourself facial masks
directions: Blend.
Pat on face and neck; leave 20 minutes.
Rinse with cool water.

title: irish soda bread(yields 1 loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter until looks like corn meal.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed.
Mix together vinegar and milk.
Add liquid to flour mixture and stir vigorously.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead 8 to 10 times.
Shape in round, greased 8-inch pie pan.
Cut crisscross (side to side).
Brush top with milk.
Place in 400° oven for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: squash bread
directions: Mix eggs, beaten with oil, vanilla and grated squash.
In another larger bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, soda, salt and nuts.
Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients and gradually stir them together.
When all ingredients are moistened, beat batter well.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° until spongy to touch.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and pecans.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 the Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust. Mix the two pudding mixes and milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining 1/2 carton of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Combine the four ingredients.
Makes about 1 cup.
Serve with beef roast or prime rib.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, evaporated milk, eggs and milk.
In a separate bowl sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add wet ingredients to dry, then mix in poppy seed and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into greased muffin tins, 3/4 full and bake 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: double duty dish
directions: Mix all together in big mixing bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: dutch beans
directions: In a Dutch oven, put oil.
Cook onion for a minute.
Then add pork and beans, the corn and the wieners and cook for 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Beat in peanut butter and vanilla.
In a small bowl, beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold into peanut butter batter.
Spoon into crust and sprinkle with peanuts.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: e~z chick pot pie
directions: Pan-fry 2 chicken breasts. Cool. Cube. Cook egg noodles; drain. Add chicken and frozen vegetables to pan. Simmer with a small amount of water. Add soup until heated. Add noodles.

title: "chocolate pot"(for chocolate lovers only)
directions: Melt chocolate in milk.
Boil until thick and creamy, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks; mix well!
Strain with cheesecloth. Pour into souffle or mousse cups.
Top with whipped cream.

title: my rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1/4-inch slices.
Place in bowl and add hot water from faucet.
Let stand.
Roll out pie crust and enough for lattice top.
Mix together sugar, 3 tablespoons water and 3 tablespoons flour and egg.
Beat until mixed.
Drain rhubarb.
Put in 9-inch crust lined pie pan.
Pour sugar mixture over.
Add lattice top crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 415°, then 40 minutes at 375°.

title: jalapeno cheese corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat greased pan before putting mix in. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in pineapple juice. Add sour cream and chill until it begins to set. Add blueberries, nuts and crushed pineapple.

title: lemon sesame chicken
directions: Mix oil, juice and seasonings and brush on chicken pieces. Let sit for an hour in the refrigerator.
Cook slowly on the grill until done, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: bible fruit cake
directions: Mix in large bowl in order given, beating in eggs until light and fluffy.
When you get to nuts and fruit mix by hand, following Solomon's advice for making a good boy (Proverbs 23:14) and you will have a good cake.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours in 4 small bread pans (7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch), buttered and bottoms lined with brown paper, buttered.
Allow to cool in pans, on sides on rack.
Run knife around edges and turn out.
Good eaten now or better aged, wrapped in cheesecloth soaked in sherry or whiskey. Wrap in foil, store in a cool place.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts with salt and a 1/4 stick of butter. Simmer for 1 hour and save the broth.
Next cut the chicken into small pieces and lay them in a rectangular dish.
Add cream of chicken soup, sour cream, and 1 cup of broth.
Mix together and spread in the dish.
Melt remaining butter in microwave. Add crumbled Ritz crackers and poppy seeds to melted butter.
Mix together and spread over the chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Combine puree, water and bay leaf; bring to a boil in medium size saucepan.
Dissolve gelatin in mixture, stirring well. Remove from heat.
Add onions and celery; season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour into large mold or individual molds and chill until firm.
Remove; garnish with slices of lemon or decorate with mayonnaise through a pastry tube.

title: classic quiche lorraine
directions: Cook and crumble bacon.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Mix eggs, milk, cream, flour and seasoning.
Stir in bacon, onion and Swiss cheese.
Pour in shell.
Cover edges of crust with foil if necessary to prevent overbrowning.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: tuscan roast pork
directions: In blender or food processor, combine garlic, oil, rosemary and salt.
Blend until it turns into a paste.
Rub over roast and let stand 30 minutes.
Place on a greased baking rack, fat side up, in a roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until internal temperature is 160° to 170°.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: mexican salad dressing
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook slowly and add butter when it starts to boil.
Cook until a soft-ball forms in cold water. Add vinegar.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until it begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered Pyrex dish.
Let cool. Cut, then eat.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve jello (any flavor).
Add cream cheese and marshmallows until dissolved.
Add all other ingredients except cream.
Cool mixture until begins to thicken.
Whip the cream and fold into mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water 1-inch deep. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold, with or without whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: individual tuna casserole
directions: Rinse tuna in cold water; drain, then flake into a 3-cup bowl. Blend in the bread, celery, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Pour tuna mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2-cup baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake in oven preheated to 325° for 20 minutes. Makes 1 serving.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Arrange layer of apples in pan and spread dough on them. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350°.

title: chinese candy
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in double boiler.
Mix in Chinese noodles and peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
After they set, store in airtight container in cool place.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Serve with tortilla chips. May be stored in refrigerator up to 24 hours.

title: broccoli with sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter, add lemon juice, pepper and sliced olives.
Arrange cooked broccoli in shallow casserole dish; pour butter/olive sauce over broccoli.
Heat in low oven (250-300 degrees) for 1/2 hour, or heat in microwave until hot. 6 servings.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Hammer breast until thin.
Cut Swiss cheese into 4-inch strips (about 1 ounce).
Roll cheese in one piece of dried beef.
Roll chicken breast around beef roll.
Arrange in casserole dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: tuna dip or spread
directions: Mayonnaise a jello mold.
Cut fish in half lengthwise and line the mold.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over fish and refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and place on a tray.
Serve with horseradish sauce and party rye or crackers.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients well.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: corn bread walnut stuffing
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and celery; saute until transparent, but not brown.
Remove from heat.
Add walnuts, parsley, poultry seasoning, salt, pepper and crumbled corn bread. Mix well; cool.
Stir in eggs; toss.
Stuff lightly into turkey. Makes enough for 10 to 12-pound turkey.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs, coffee, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes (batter very thin).
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve topped with Cool Whip.

title: string bean casserole
directions: In a casserole dish melt butter, then put in drained beans, soup and milk (do not stir).
Put in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and put enough cheese slices on to cover.
Sprinkle onion rings and then almonds on top.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: divinity
directions: Mix well 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water, then heat to boiling until mixture strings.
Pour over three well beaten egg whites. In separate pan, mix 3 cups sugar, 1 cup white syrup and 3/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling until brittle when tried in cold water. Add 2nd mixture to 1st mixture, pouring gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and vanilla.
Pour by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips and cheese.
Put in casserole; top with potato chips and cheese.
Bake until cheese melts at 400°.

title: tomato rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat. Saute onions and garlic until onions are soft. Off heat, stir in flour to make a roux. Return to heat and stir for about 5 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Fill 2 pie shells 1/2 full of apples.
Divide 1/2 sugar mixture between 2 pies.
Finish filling with apples and then divide the remaining 1/2 mixture into pies.
Divide margarine and vanilla between 2 pies.
Place top crust on and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Put the syrup on the stove and let boil a little thick.
Drop in the peaches and heat through.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pea and lettuce salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Mix with salad ingredients.
Cover.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: doctor's chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle pecans and chips into the shell.
Blend corn syrup, sugar and eggs.
Stir in melted butter. Pour into the shell.
Stir to mix nuts and chips evenly.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve with homemade whipped cream.

title: kelle's cream of mushroom soup
directions: In Dutch oven, melt butter over medium heat.
Add celery and cook until almost tender.
Add mushrooms and continue cooking until all tender.
Add garlic salt, salt and white pepper.
Add flour a little at a time while stirring and cook for a few minutes (to cook out flour taste) while stirring constantly.
Mix bouillon with hot water.
Slowly add to mushroom mixture, stirring constantly.
Add 1 cup of half and half and let simmer and thicken about 20 minutes. Mix together remaining 1/2 cup half and half with cornstarch.
Add to soup.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 2 deep dish pies.

title: oven baked chuck steak
directions: Place foil in roasting pan, enough to wrap over steak, potatoes and carrots.
Place steak in pan.
Combine soups and pour over steak.
Add potatoes and carrots; wrap.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: pizzelles cookies
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, a little at a time; mix well.
Add oil, butter and extracts.
Beat again.
Beat in flour, a little at a time.
Put by teaspoon onto pizzelle iron and press until slightly brown.

title: pumpkin-pecan bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Make a well in center and add oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well; add the nuts.
Spray two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans with no-stick cooking spray.
Pour into pans, filling each 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center of the loaf comes out clean. Yield:
2 loaves (16 slices each).
One slice equals 85 calories.

title: sin pie(sinfully delicious)
directions: Mash together and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 375° oven.
Cool.

title: buttercrisp potato cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in egg, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1 inch balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of drinking glass which has been slightly moistened and dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until just barely golden brown around edges for chewy cookies.
(Bake longer for crispier cookies.)

title: sugarless freezer date cookies
directions: Cream butter, egg and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients. Blend both mixtures thoroughly.
Mix dates, coconut and walnuts until blended.
Form dough into two (1 1/2-inch) rolls and wrap in waxed paper or foil.
Chill in freezer 2 hours or up to 1 month.
Slice with sharp knife into 3/8-inch slices.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: easy congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in
hot	water.	Add
remaining ingredients. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: refrigerator oatmeal cookies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape in rolls, then wrap in waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly or overnight.
Slice them in 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Bake at 330° for 10 minutes.

title: summer sausage(hamburger or venison burger)
directions: Mix all ingredients and divide into 3 parts (in 3 Ziploc bags). Refrigerate for 3 whole days. Knead in the bags everyday.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and then form into balls.
Bake until done; this takes about 12 minutes.
Makes 65 balls.
tags: Kraft Cracker Barrel sharp Cheddar cheese

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add a few drops of water if necessary.
Form into balls the size of walnuts and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: beef and vegetable soup
directions: Dredge meat with flour that has been mixed with salt and paprika; shake off excess.
Heat oil in large saucepan until hot. Brown meat in hot oil on all sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Add beef stock, tomatoes, Worcestershire, onion and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until meat is almost tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, celery and potatoes; mix gently.
Simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, 20 minutes.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Crumble the sausage
and
mix with cheese.
Add biscuit mix, one cup at a time.
Form into small balls (about one inch in diameter) and bake
on
an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° to
until
light
brown (13 to 15 minutes).
Cooking may take
a
few extra minutes if balls are frozen.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: quick creamy potato soup
directions: In a large pan, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble. Set aside.

title: fudge
directions: Bring to a rolling boil until soft ball forms in cold water (10 to 12 minutes).
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine.
Stir until creamy smooth (approximately 1 minute).
Pour into buttered plate.

title: baked cashews with chicken
directions: Place chicken in individual casseroles.
Combine butter, paprika, curry powder, oregano, garlic powder and pepper, mixing well.
Spoon over chicken dishes.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven (or toaster oven) along with yams, for 60 minutes, or until chicken and yams are tender.

title: cheese spaghetti
directions: Put tomatoes (cut up) in pot.
Bring to boil, turn down, let simmer 5 minutes.
At same time put water on for spaghetti.
When you add spaghetti to water, add cheese (cut up in chunks) to tomatoes.
Keep stirring cheese until all melted.
Drain spaghetti when done, add tomatoe/cheese sauce (put in bowl to combine).
Brown butter and pour over spaghetti.
Mix together. Let sit for 5 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat first four ingredients until boiling, stirring constantly.
Then boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour slowly over corn (corn on large cookie sheet with edge).
Bake slowly in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add meat, salt, pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook over moderately hot heat, stirring constantly, until meat is brown.
Add bouillon and green peppers.
Cover closely and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 1 minute longer.
Blend together cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Add to skillet and cook 3 or 4 minutes longer, stirring constantly, until mixture is hot and sauce is thickened.
Serve at once over hot rice.

title: bacon tidbits
directions: Cut off crust from bread.
Cut each slice into two triangles. Spoon a dab of soup into center of each; roll up corners.
Wrap bacon (cut in half lengthwise and again widthwise) around each triangle and secure with toothpicks.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat egg yolks with 1 cup sugar until creamy.
Stir into rich cream.
Add vanilla or rum flavoring.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; pour into freezer.
Add enough milk to fill freezer.

title: vegetable confetti bites
directions: Roll crescent rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake crust for 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix sugar and milk together, stir while cooking to soft stage; add nuts and dates and cook to hard boil stage; add vanilla and cool.
Beat until creamy and stiff, place on wet towel and shape into roll.
Wrap in wax paper, slice before serving.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Blend together and bring to a boil. Allow to cool before pouring over vegetables. Put in a covered container and refrigerate.
Keeps a long time!

title: make-your-own tostadas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in oil; drain well.
Stir in enchilada mix, water and tomato sauce.
Boil gently, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir in beans and milk.
Reheat to serving temperature.

title: imitation lobster
directions: Take one pound of fresh bass fillets and shape in the form of a lobster tail on cookie sheet.
(If fillets are large, cut in half.)
Freeze. Bring a large pan of water to rolling boil.
Add shrimp and frozen fish fillets.
Boil about five minutes.
Do not overboil!
Remove from water and place in glass oven dish.
Baste with garlic butter and broil in oven until top is light brown. Serve with a dip of garlic butter and enjoy!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream all ingredients, except shrimp and mayonnaise, until well blended.
Stir in mashed shrimp.
Add mayonnaise until desired consistency, usually about 2 tablespoons.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli per instructions on package.
Drain well.
In a large saucepan, stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat, stirring continuously until warm enough to serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a 10 x 6-inch dish.
Fill 3/4 full of sliced apples. Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg.
Spread over apples.
Pour melted butter over and sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix with canola oil and egg whites.
Add can of mandarin oranges.
Mix well and bake.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake at 350° for 34 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 small loaves or a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy apple coffee cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream and oil; beat 5 minutes with electric beater.
Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon; pour 1/2 of batter into greased 10-inch tube pan or rectangular pan.
Arrange 1/2 of apples on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 of nut mixture. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack for 30 minutes.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients except kidney beans in a Dutch oven or stock pot.
Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours until ingredients are tender and well blended.
Add kidney beans to mixture.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Can be made in slow cooker or crock pot before adding beans.

title: cox burgers
directions: Mix ground chuck, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Form into 4 patties.
Marinate with Worcestershire sauce at least 30 minutes before cooking, turning at least once during marinating time. Cook on outside grill or may be broiled in oven. Simple and very tasty burgers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: First put 4 pints of water in pot.
Add potatoes, carrots, cabbage, onion, celery, bacon grease, salt and sugar.
Cook 20 minutes, then add corn, peas and cooked tomatoes.
Cook for 20 more minutes.
All together cook for 40 minutes.

title: pluck-it cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom.
Cut biscuits in quarters, mix white sugar and cinnamon and put in plastic bag. Drop biscuits in mixture to coat.
Drop into Bundt pan on top of pecans.
Put leftover cinnamon mixture on top.
Melt butter and brown sugar until brown sugar dissolves and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine ingredients in slow cooker and heat at low temperature for about 3 hours.
Serve hot.
Yields 12 servings.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in churn container.
Finish filling to full line with milk; churn.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter, cocoa powder, vanilla and salt. Spread into 9-inch baking pan and chill until fudge hardens.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: baked squash
directions: Melt margarine and mix with dressing.
Set aside.
Mix squash, soup, sour cream and onion.
Put 1/2 of the crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour on squash mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy shrimp scampi(scampi con aglio)
directions: In large skillet add butter, oil, garlic and scallions; saute over medium low heat until lightly browned.
Remove from heat. Dust shrimp with flour
and
place
in
frying pan with butter mixture; return to heat.
Pan
fry over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add pepper
and stir, scraping pan.
Place on warmed platter and sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marylee's tea cakes
directions: Place flour in "biscuit tray" or mixing bowl.
Pack flour in center to make a hole for the remaining ingredients.
Be careful to leave the flour on the sides in place.
Add sugar, eggs, milk, shortening and flavoring in this order.
Hand mix, adding flour from sides as needed.
Knead to a smooth texture (stiff, not sticky).
Place dough on a floured rolling board or wax paper. Roll to 1/8-inch in thickness.
Cut tea cakes out and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes in a preheated oven.

title: ziti noodle casserole(serves 4)
directions: Brown onion and parsley.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings in oil.
Cover and simmer 3 hours.
Cook noodles.
In greased 8 x 8-inch casserole dish add alternate layers of noodles, cheese and sauce.
Save some cheese for top layer.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken in foil for 4
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Tear off 4 sheets of foil.
Butter or spray the foil with cooking spray.
Divide ingredients into 4 groups.
Place onion on foil and chicken breast on top.
Brush the chicken breasts with Dijon mustard.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer on top of chicken: squash, zucchini and mushrooms. Add pieces of butter on top.
Sprinkle on basil, garlic and paprika.
Fold over and seal aluminum foil to form a pouch.
Place the packs on a baking sheet.
Bake for 18 minutes at 450°, then turn down oven to 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (if desired).
Serve over hot rice.

title: jimmie's corn muffins
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
sour
cream, creamed corn and cooking oil. Add to cornmeal and baking powder sifted together.
Bake in greased
muffin pans or cornstick pans at 375° until golden brown. Makes 12 large or 18 small muffins.

title: ed's baked ham and turkey rolls
directions: Have both ham and turkey sliced at least 1/8 inch thick. Either use Stove Top stuffing or mix up a batch of your own best dressing and a pan of giblet gravy.
I sometimes use chicken or mushroom gravy.
Ready made gravy made be used if you like.
Lay 1 slice of ham down and place 1 slice of turkey on top of ham overlapping about 1/2 way up the slice.
Now place enough dressing on the meat to make a good serving and roll it up.
Place all the meat rolls in a large baking dish.
Pour gravy over the meat rolls. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven until hot.
Remove from oven and place a slice of cheese and a slice tomato on top of each roll, return to oven until cheese begins to melt.
Sprinkle parsley on top and serve hot. This is great for a large group and can be made in advance.
Freezes well.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Scoop out tomatoes and save. Turn tomatoes upside down to drain. Saute the onions, celery and peppers in butter until soft, not brown. Chop tomato pulp. Combine with onions, celery, peppers, crackers and salt and pepper.
Stuff tomatoes and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Drizzle with melted butter and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: gramma's baked beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Drain and add more water to cover.
Boil 1 hour or until tender.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over and stir.
Lay enough bacon strips on top to cover beans (can be done with turkey bacon also).
Bake for 1 hour or until bacon is crisp and beans are browned in 350° oven.

title: western dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
Drain grease.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave or double boiler.
Put chopped Ro-Tel tomatoes in a crock-pot.
Add cheese and meat mixture.
Simmer on low for at least 30 minutes.
Eat with nachos.

title: curried lentils and rice
directions: Melt butter and oil in a saucepan.
Add curry, salt, pepper, cloves and Tabasco.
Heat for a minute, stirring.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is limp.
Add lentils and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil.
Then cover and simmer 45 minutes or until lentils are tender.
Cook rice in 1 1/2 cups water while lentils are cooking.
Combine rice and lentils in serving bowl and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve.

title: cherry nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar; beat until creamy.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well with each addition.
Add baking powder and flavorings.
Alternate flour and milk; beat 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in the cherries.

title: corn chowder
directions: 1. Fry bacon and set aside. Drain most of bacon fat out of pan.
2. Cook pepper, onion, and celery in remaining bacon fat until slightly brown.
3. Dissolve flour in 1/4 c. heated broth. Add rest of
broth & add to cooked vegetables. Add diced potatoes and simmer. Cook until potatoes are tender.
4. Add the corn, clams (if desired), milk, margarine,
sugar, parsley, white pepper, salt, and pepper. Bring
to a light boil.

title: beans beans beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or in crock-pot on low for 4 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles; set aside in cold water to keep from sticking by putting on wax paper.
Fry hamburger meat; drain fat.
Add peppers, onions and spaghetti sauce to meat.
Set aside.
Mix all the cottage cheese in bowl with 1/4 Parmesan cheese; add eggs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix well.

title: graham bars
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended. Spread mixture in a well greased pan.
Bake in oven at 350° about 35 minutes or until cake pulls from sides of pan.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cheese over.
Crumble and brown sausage; drain and sprinkle over cheese and bread.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard and pour over other ingredients.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, cook around 30 minutes at 350°.
Cook longer if needed to set; may need to remove foil.
Should cut like quiche.

title: cindy's potato salad
directions: Wash (do not peel) potatoes.
Cook in boiling salted water with herbs.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
To the potatoes, add diced cucumber, onions with tops (sliced) and parsley (chopped finely).
Melt butter.
Pour over salad and toss.
Add sour cream and toss.
May be served at room temperature or cold.

title: wonderful bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Nabisco 100% Bran cereal in bowl and let stand.
Cream oil and sugar in large bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs and 100% Bran cereal.
Add flour and remaining ingredients and mix.
Put batter in airtight covered bowl in refrigerator; batter keeps for 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: supper rolls
directions: Combine sour cream and egg in large bowl.
Add pancake mix; blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with seed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: no fail kraut
directions: Dissolve
salt and vinegar in water.
Pour over chopped cabbage in
sterilized
jars and seal.
It's ready to eat in 4 weeks and doesn't turn dark.

title: sauce for baked ham
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool.
Dilute with half and half, if too thick.
Serve over baked ham.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Prepare pudding mix (not instant) according to directions. Blend cake mix into prepared pudding.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli, onion, oleo, salt and pepper together.
Mix and heat chicken broth, cream of mushroom soup, sliced mushrooms and milk.
Next, add shredded Cheddar cheese and dissolved cornstarch. Simmer until hot.

title: clara's caramel sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar and syrup. Cook until sugar is dissolved but do not boil. Remove from heat.
Mix half of the milk with half of the syrup mixture, then add to remaining syrup. Do not curdle milk. Serve over gingerbread, chocolate, yellow or spice cake or ice cream.
May be served warm or cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind or chop cranberries and orange.
Add pineapple, celery, nuts and sugar.
Mix well and set aside.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine all together. Put into casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika and salt to taste.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place casserole in oven and bake until it begins to bubble, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1/3 cup Milnot, melted oleo and nuts. Will look almost like pie dough.
Put half of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: martin luther hot dish
directions: Bake the ribs with salt, pepper and chopped onion.
When done, add potatoes and sauerkraut.
Heat until potatoes are cooked.

title: fried biscuits
directions: Add yeast to warm water to dissolve.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt; add yeast.
Gradually add flour until a round ball forms.
May be beaten in mixer with dough hook attachment. Cover with cloth and let dough rise until double.
Drop from tablespoon into melted shortening and fry like doughnuts until golden brown.
Serve with preserves, apple butter, honey, or syrup. Yields 7 dozen biscuits.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Melt margarine in electric frying pan; set at 325°.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add beef and cook until redness disappears.
Add salt, pepper, flour, mushrooms and soup. Stir and cook slowly 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve hot over cooked noodles.
Top with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: joyce's popcorn balls
directions: Boil ingredients until it looks like a thread spinning.
Put in a pinch of soda.
Pour over popcorn and make balls.

title: chicken continental
directions: Combine undiluted soups, milk, rice, curry powder and onion salt in a 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: maple pumpkin cheese cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup and milk.
Mix well. Stir in 1/2 can onions and green beans.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes until brown.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream together eggs, shortening and sugar.
Stir in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Knead down until soft dough is formed. Shape into round rolls and let stand a few hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Slice with sharp knife.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pigs 'n' blankets
directions: Cut core out of cabbage and place it in a large pot with a couple inches of water. Cover and steam. Remove cabbage leaves as they become soft and pliable.

title: mrs. perry's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, cocoa and sugar in boiler.
Beat egg yolks and pour into mix.
Add half milk.
Mix all ingredients.
Add rest of milk.
Cook on stove on low to medium heat until thick.
After thickening, add vanilla and butter and pour into a baked pie shell.
Let mixture cool.
Use egg whites for a meringue.
Bake 15 minutes or until top is light brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef until crumbly.
Stir in dry taco seasoning mix.
Add tomatoes and corn.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions.
Pour cornbread over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash the sweet potatoes in mixer or food processor.
Melt butter and add to potatoes. Add sugar and salt. Beat eggs and add vanilla and flour.
Mix thoroughly. Grease baking dish and pour mixture in.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle.
Steep just below boiling point for 2 hours.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.

title: round steak supper
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces; season with salt and pepper. Roll in flour.
Saute onions in hot shortening in skillet until tender.
Remove from heat.
Brown steak pieces slowly on both sides.
Put in 3-quart casserole.
Add onions and potatoes.
Pour soup over top.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until steak is tender.
Add green beans.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: scrubby's hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground chuck into bite-size chunks with onion.
Add water and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together and put into mold.
Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix and congeal Jell-O, boiling water, pineapple and pie filling.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of congealed salad.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: apple and cheddar chicken
directions: Saute apples and onions in margarine until just tender.
Mix Cheddar, Parmesan, bread crumbs and thyme.
Place apples and onions in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with chicken and pour apple juice over.
Spread dry mixture over top and moisten with margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: fruit and cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in large bowl until well blended. Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread in crust.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chickens with some onion, celery and salt.
Saute in butter, onions, green pepper and drained mushrooms.
In a large pan, put liquid from drained mushrooms and olives; add chicken broth.
Bring to boil and add noodles, sauteed mixture, olives and frozen peas (thawed).
Add 1 cup cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) and chicken.
Put half of this mixture in baking dish. Add layer of cheese, other half of cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: cranberry ketchup
directions: In a medium nonreactive saucepan, combine 2/3 cup water with the cranberries, onion, vinegar, garlic, allspice and salt. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring frequently, for 15 minutes longer.
Let cool for 30 minutes.
Transfer the mixture to a blender and puree, then strain into a glass measure.
Pour the ketchup into glass bottles.
Will keep refrigerated for up to two months.
Makes 1 1/2 pints.

title: squash pie
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornflakes and butter together. Cover with the cornflakes and butter.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon and hamburger.
Cook rice with 1 teaspoon salt and some butter.
Mix it all together and bake 45 minutes.

title: golden mushroom sirloin beef tips
directions: In skillet, brown beef cubes in butter.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low heat 2 hours or until tender, stirring now and then.
Serve over cooked rice or cooked noodles. Serves 4.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 1 large bundt pan or 2 small bundt pans.
Bake at 350 degrees until toothpick in center of cake comes out clean.

title: crock-pot o' gold pork roast
directions: Cook meat, onions and carrots on low crock-pot setting for 8 to 10 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti hot dish
directions: Cook, debone, and chop the chicken. Saute mushrooms in 2 Tbsp. butter. Cook spaghetti, drain and add a dab of butter set aside. Measure and melt the 1/2 c. butter over low heat in a large kettle. Add flour and seasonings bring to a boil for full minute. Add broth and bring back to a boil, cook till thickened. Reduce heat to low. Stir in cream and soup. Add mushrooms, chicken, and spaghetti, mix well. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 425 degree oven.

title: tomatoes and okra
directions: Slice okra in 1/2-inch slices.
Cook, covered, in small amount of
boiling
salted
water for 10 minutes or cook 1 (10 ounce) package
frozen
okra according to package directions. Drain. Cook
onions
and chopped peppers in oil until tender, but not brown.
Blend in sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Add 3 peeled
and quartered
tomatoes
and
okra.
Heat thoroughly. Serves 4.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, oil and margarine or butter.
With buttered spoon or buttered hands, press all into a buttered tube pan.
Turn out after it has firmed up.

title: jello
directions: Stir water into jello until dissolved.
Stir in juice and refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in fruit.
Chill until well set.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt and sugar and beat until dissolved.
Add milk and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into a 10-inch pie shell, unbaked, and sprinkle with nutmeg (nutmeg may be added with the sugar).
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer or until knife inserted in pie comes out clean.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients. Add crabmeat and all but 3/4 cup of stuffing mix. Add mustard, eggs, garlic powder, salt and pepper and as much chicken broth as needed. Pour in casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup stuffing mix. Dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: icehouse peach soup(4 servings)
directions: Puree peaches with lemon juice in a food processor or blender until smooth.
Pour into a medium-sized bowl.
With a mortar and pestle, thoroughly crush together cardamom and coriander.
Add to peach puree along with remaining ingredients.
Stir until well combined.
Chill thoroughly for at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and butter and toss with blueberries. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Top with pastry or crumb topping.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Make pie crust for 2 pies.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except butter.
Mix well and spoon into pie crust. Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Cut a slit in top crust. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Toss all together the first 4 ingredients.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Put the green beans on top of the mixture. Add the almonds on top of the layer of beans.
Add the chicken.
Mix together the soup, mayonnaise and broth.
Pour cream mixture over top of each layer including the top and final layer. Top with bread crumbs. Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: orangy pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the shortening with sugar; add eggs, pumpkin and water. Sift together next 6 ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Remove seeds from orange.
Using blender or grinder, grind orange, including peel; add to pumpkin batter.
Stir in nuts and raisins or dates.
Pour into two well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or seven 1-pound cans and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large or 7 small loaves.

title: basic loaf(meatless)
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: corn custard
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Add all other ingredients except whites and mix well.
Last fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a buttered dish in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Best if placed in pan of water while baking.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken; when chicken is finished boiling, add both cans chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Roll out biscuits in flour and cut.
When liquid boils, add salt to taste.
Add dumplings and 1/2 cup milk.
Let cook 20 to 30 minutes, then add chicken.
Let set 15 to 20 minutes before eating.

title: st. john banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients.
Beat in mashed bananas.
Add nuts. Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
While the bread is still warm, pour melted butter over top and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
If too thick, add buttermilk to moisten.
Let stand half a day before cooking.

title: orange creamsicle cake
directions: Follow directions on box for baking cake.
Bake two 8-inch round layers.
Cool.
Split each layer in half, making 4 layers.

title: japanese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pork chops and mixed veggies
directions: Trim fat from pork chops and coat with Shake 'N Bake as per directions.
Pour undrained vegetables in a baking dish.
Place chops on top of veggies.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 50 minutes.

title: simple corn
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for about 2 hours. No salt needed.
Tastes like fresh out of the garden.

title: cranberry muffins and sauce
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Sift together the next 3 ingredients, then add all ingredients.
Mix until smooth. Fold cranberries into mixture.
Put into lined muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kids' jello
directions: Mix all together and let set.
Can be cut into cubes and use different colors together or serve cubes of this recipe and cubes of plain jello.

title: crab casserole
directions: Heat white sauce and cheese until smooth; add celery salt, green pepper, mushrooms and crabmeat.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into large casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Put butter, oil, onion and garlic together.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Remove garlic.
Add the tomato paste and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add broth and simmer until mushrooms are cooked, about 10 minutes.
Mix yolks and parsley together, then add to soup.
Add wine to soup to taste.
Don't allow soup to boil once eggs have been added.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until blended, stirring constantly. Set off stove to cool. When cool, add mayonnaise. Mix water and gelatine and add to mixture. Add shrimp last. Place in refrigerator.

title: mulled cider
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients for about 30 minutes. Add orange and lemon slices.
Serve hot.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Wash and boil chicken for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove chicken from
broth
and
boil
broccoli
in
the
broth until tender.
Drain
and
discard
liquid.
Mix	soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice
and
curry
powder.
Chop the chicken into chunks and mix
with the soup mixture.
Add broccoli to mixture.
Put into greased
casserole	dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Top with cheese and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda; sift again.
Add flour and buttermilk to cream mixture. Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: homemade fertilizer
directions: With a cotton ball saturated with rubbing alcohol, rub the inside of the shoe and put them on bare feet.
Wear the shoes until completely dry.
They retain the shape they have acquired and are truly comfortable. It works!

title: cleo
directions: Spread cherries in long baking dish (9 x 13 inch).
Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherries.
Pour melted oleo over cake mix. Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake in a 350 degree oven 1 hour. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil on high speed.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend.
Add pecans, apples and dates; stir well to blend.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until cake tester is clean.
Let stand 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Use large aluminum turkey roaster (disposable one with no bumps).
Grease and flour pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions and bake in pan until light golden brown.
Cool. Prepare pudding mix according to package directions and spread over cake.
Spread drained pineapple over pudding.
Slice bananas over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and almonds.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the first six ingredients and add pecan pieces.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: praline cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crunchy topped apricot dessert
directions: *Add 1 tablespoon icing sugar if using cream.

title: beef quiche
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet and brown beef.
Drain in a colander.
Add salt, peppers and onion.
Stir well. Beat eggs well.
Add milk, then mayonnaise, cornstarch and cheese.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serves 6.
Serve with stuffed tomato or a fruit salad with asparagus or broccoli.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O. Add well-drained fruits.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour and salad is ready to eat.

title: overnight breakfast casserole
directions: In 9 x 12 x 3-inch pan, sprinkle sausage, ham or bacon and shredded cheese.
Beat together milk, eggs, dry mustard, salt and dash of pepper.
Pour over bread, meat and cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: scalloped vegetables
directions: Place cooked vegetables and prepare white sauce in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer potatoes and onion.
Add pats of butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle flour.
Add layer of cheese.
Continue until dish is full.
Fill 1/2 bowl with milk. Bake for 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: grilled marinated pork chops
directions: In a glass dish, thoroughly combine all ingredients, placing pork chops in last.
Cover and marinate for at least four hours in refrigerator.
Place chops on grill 5 to 7 inches above charcoal. Sear quickly on high on both sides.
Turn fire down to low temperature and continue to cook for 20 to 25 minutes on each side or until done, turning chops occasionally, and brushing frequently with marinade.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: new german sweet chocolate pudding cake
directions: *Or you may use 1/2 cup sour cream and 3/4 cup of water.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Dice cheeses and place in pie shell.
Add ham on top of cheese.
Beat eggs and
add
half
and
half, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.	Pour mixture in pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes	6 servings.
Serve with fresh fruit or green salad.

title: pizza quickies
directions: Butter each muffin half.
Combine next 4 ingredients and spread on muffins.
Top each with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Makes 8 mini pizzas.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt chocolate.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix. Add flour and milk alternately.
Add 1/2 cup hot water.
Heat 1/2 cup water in pan to boiling point; add soda immediately and immediately add to chocolate mixture.
Pour mixture in batter and add vanilla.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: In 8 x 8-inch bowl, mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together rice and canned soups; put in baking dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Sprinkle the French onion soup mix over chicken. Melt the butter; pour over mixture.
Wrap tightly in foil; bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: steak seasoning
directions: Mix the packages of the mixes together, sprinkle generously on steaks, then pour cola over steaks.
marinate for a while, then grill.

title: lasagne #2
directions: Cook and drain lasagne while browning ground beef.
When brown, drain excess fat (rinse for less cholesterol).
Add spaghetti sauce, water, spices, salt and pepper to taste.
Layer in 9 x 14-inch pan the sauce, noodles and cheeses in that order twice.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove foil and let cheese brown.
Let set a few minutes and serve. Makes approximately 8 average servings.

title: spicy sweet pork
directions: Place pork in large resealable plastic bag.
Combine fajita sauce and marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
In a large skillet or wok heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add bell pepper and green onion; stir-fry about 3 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Add pork and remaining 1 tablespoon oil to skillet.
Stir-fry for about 5 minutes or until browned.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir-fry until warm.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar,
flour
and	milk.
Add melted butter.
Pour into greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Pour in fruit and sugar. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Boil water and cream cheese until melted.
Add jello.
Mix well.
Add cranberries and walnuts to taste.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Let set.
Spread on Cool Whip when cool.
Very good at holidays!

title: died and gone to heaven dessert
directions: Mix devil's food cake mix following directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture on cool cake.

title: none better beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, add onion, garlic, tomatoes and steak sauce. Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni and add to beef mixture.
Spoon in soup and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in a dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut candy fine.
Mix flour, nuts and baking powder with candy. Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix together well.
Add first mixture and blend.
Put in 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan, greased (put wax paper down and grease again).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Chip beef and sprinkle over the bottom of casserole dish. Wrap bacon around the chicken and place over the beef. Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 300°.
Take cover off during the last half hour.

title: oyster crackers party mix
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over oyster crackers.
Bake at low heat 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator raisin-bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator up to 2 months and use as desired.
Do not freeze.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Combine flour and spices.
Mix together alternating with buttermilk and soda.
Add chopped prunes and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in layer pans. Cool.
Frost with Caramel Icing.

title: red skin potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with onion and Mrs. Dash (after boiling throw onion away).
Chop hard boiled eggs.
Chop parsley and add black olives, Miracle Whip, Mrs. Dash and chopped eggs.
Mix well.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Butter bottom and sides of baking dish. Spoon a thin layer of soup on bottom of dish. Place in one can of asparagus. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add another layer of soup. Place sliced egg on that and sprinkle with cheese. Repeat the entire process again and top with crushed potato chips. Bake in moderate oven about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fried corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by large spoonfuls in shallow hot oil in skillet or deep fryer.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: steak durango
directions: Melt butter and mix in remaining ingredients.
Brush on each side of steak and marinate 1 hour or more.
Cook to desired doneness over charcoal fire.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on box using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
When done, punch holes with toothpick at random, about 1/2 inch apart.
Pour cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk over top of cake.
When cooked, put in refrigerator.
Before serving, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Angel Flake coconut.
Keeps very well in fridge.

title: everyday vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: In small bowl or jar, combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all together and let come to a boil for exactly 2 minutes, not stirring after sugar is dissolved.
Take off of stove and hasten cooling by putting in a pan of ice water for a few minutes. Then start beating until creamy.
Do not attempt to put on the cake until thick enough not to run off.
If it gets too thick, a drop of hot water will soften it.

title: pasta salad
