directions: Cook noodles; add vinegar and olive oil to taste. Add Lawry's seasoning salt, pepper and a dash of garlic powder. Mix all ingredients.

title: fast sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook slowly until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix in Mix Master (all ingredients).
Refrigerate twelve hours.
Form into ball and roll in pecans.

title: chicken oahu
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate covered and refrigerated for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Place casserole in 325° oven for 3/4 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve with brown rice.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground meat and onions.
Drain fat.
In a large pot, combine ground meat, tomato juice, beans and chili powder.
Cook on low heat, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, cornstarch and water until thick and clear. Add jello.
Cool a few minutes and add strawberries.
Put in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 2 medium loaf pans, well greased and floured, at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: apple bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add brown sugar and oats.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Spread half of mixture into greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Add apples and sprinkle with sugar.
Add remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into bars and serve warm; or serve cold as a cookie.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on to a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken in the crock-pot
directions: Cook on low in crock-pot for 4 to 6 hours.
Remove chicken. Add 2 tablespoons flour and use a whisk to make mmm gravy!

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients.
Chill dough and roll into balls.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown (very light), approximately 10 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Blend thoroughly butter and sugar.
Knead in flour.
Press with your hand into 2 round cakes, 3/4 inch thick.
Pierce with a fork.
Bake in a moderate oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, slice into 8 to 12 wedges.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Punch holes in hot cake.
Pour pineapple and sugar mixture over cake.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Pound
chicken	breasts
flat
between	sheets of waxed paper. Season
with
salt,
pepper, basil and oregano.
Place thin slice of cheese on top, roll up and seal edges.	Roll in flour and pat off excess.
Brown slowly in heated oil;
remove after
evenly browned.
In same pan, add mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Replace
chicken and simmer about 20 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: angel delight
directions: Whip cream until stiff.
Add the confectioners sugar.
Fold the pineapple, sliced strawberries and marshmallows with 3/4 cup whipped cream.
Leave enough for icing sides of cake.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and peanut butter together.
Add sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Grate the Hershey bar and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Dice celery.
Hard-boil and chop eggs.
Chop pickles.
Mix altogether; add mayo or salad dressing to moisten to taste.
Makes 8 servings.

title: kathy's date bars
directions: Heat dates, sugar, eggs and butter to boiling on low; boil for 2 minutes.
Set aside to cool, then add Rice Krispies and nuts. In flat 9 x 12-inch pan, put 1/2 cup coconut; sprinkle over entire pan.
Pour date mixture over this and sprinkle 1/2 cup more coconut over the top.
Let cool and then enjoy!

title: black beans and rice
directions: Cook all ingredients together until beans are done to desired softness. Serve over already prepared rice. Goes well with biscuits.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square dish. Sprinkle batter with 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Microwave at full power 5 to 7 minutes rotating dish every 2 minutes until done. Cool and cut.
Or bake in conventional oven at 350° until golden brown and done.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Mix together top ingredients.
Cut up 3/4 of 1/2 pound box of Velveeta cheese and cook until it thickens.
When cool, add pineapple.
Nuts can be added, if desired.

title: dalrymple banana salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except bananas and peanuts) and cook until it thickens.
Let mixture cool.
Put alternate layers of sliced bananas, ground peanuts and filling in a serving bowl and cover.
Top with ground peanuts.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin something
directions: Mix together:
milk, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, eggs, and pumpkin.
Then add 1/2 pkg. cake mix, oleo and nuts.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: herb's spaghetti
directions: Brown tomato paste in oil.
Cook it kind of slow, and stir while browning.
Add a pinch of sugar to cut the whang.
When paste is brown, add 2 quarts of water.
Add the onion.
Bring to a rolling boil, add spaghetti noodles, then turn down heat.
Add garlic, salt, and creole to taste.
Cook just until spaghetti is tender.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet and mix in other ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Freezes well.

title: caramel pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (butter and vanilla should be added after removing from stove; thickened).
Pour into baked shells. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Pour melted margarine in pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over margarine.
Add pineapple and cherries.
Combine cake mix, eggs, pineapple juice and water to make 1 1/3 cups liquid. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert on plate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Combine milk, melted butter and egg.
Add to dry ingredients slowly, beating until smooth.
Bake in greased square pan in 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown beef and onion until done.
Drain fat.
Meanwhile, mix meal, corn, egg and milk.
Grease heavy iron skillet and sprinkle with meal.
Put half of cornbread mix in skillet, add beef and onion, jalapeno pepper and cheese.
Pour remaining cornbread mix over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Put cottage cheese in bowl.
Add unbeaten eggs, cheese (cut in chunks), margarine (cut in large pieces) and spinach (partially thawed and broken in pieces).
Then, flour.
Mix well.
Salt slightly to taste.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.
This recipe is a "kid-pleaser."

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Add water, tomato sauce, seasoning mix and noodles. Stir gently. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook covered 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine egg, salt and milk.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Roll very thin on floured surface.
Let stand at least 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs
thoroughly.	Add
sugar
and flour; blend in melted margarine
and corn.
Add milk, pour in casserole dish. Cook at 375° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Spoon 2 level tablespoons of batter into each muffin cup.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and press 1 peanut butter cup candy in center of each muffin.
Bake an additional 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain. Pat dry with paper towels. Place Knorr vegetable soup contents, sour cream, spinach and mayonnaise in bowl and mix. Add water chestnuts, if desired.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: grandma's cheesecake
directions: Line
bottom
of
x
9-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs moistened with butter to form a crust.
Save enough for top of cake.
Prepare
pineapple
or
lemon jello using only 1 cup of water.
When
it
starts
to
jell, add 1 cup of sugar. Beat softened cream cheese, jello and whipped cream until well mixed (thick).
Add crushed pineapple and mix well.
Pour over cracker crumb crust.
Add
rest
of
crumbs
to
top
of cake. Chill in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into uniform cubes.
Cook in boiling salted water until done.
Drain off potatoes.
Let cool in refrigerator. Add your 2 boiled eggs chopped up.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: italian orange salad
directions: Arrange sliced oranges on a platter.
Drizzle olive oil over oranges.
Place olives on oranges.
Sprinkle a little garlic salt and black pepper.
Excellent when served with fish.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare broccoli as directed. Put broccoli into 9 x 12 baking dish. Mix in cream of mushroom soup (undiluted). Cube 1 cup of Velveeta cheese and mix in. Crumble about 12 crackers into casserole and stir slightly. Crumble and top casserole with 20 crackers or until casserole is covered with crackers. Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together butter or oil, sugar and vanilla and add well beaten eggs.
Add flour and cocoa; mix well. Bake in a 9-inch pan that is well-greased.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add well-beaten eggs. Mix enough flour to keep from curdling. Mix well and add mincemeat. Sift the remaining flour with the other dry ingredients and add to the mixture. Dough should be the consistency of roll dough. (If you are adding chopped nuts, add now.) Drop from a teaspoon on a GREASED cookie sheet (push a maraschino cherry or a nut in the center). Allow two inches between cookies for spreading space. Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as it says on box. Cool. Cut layers in half to make 4 layers. Combine sugar, sour cream, coconut and refrigerate.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Heat soup and water with Cheez Whiz.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: italian sausage and zucchini casserole
directions: In skillet, cook onion and sausage.
Remove and drain.
Saute zucchini in remaining fat until transparent.
Set zucchini aside. Combine 1/2 spaghetti sauce with rice and sausage.
Put this 1/2 in 2-quart baking dish and add salt and basil.
Mix well.
Arrange 1/2 zucchini over top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 Mozzarella and 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers of rice with spices, sauce, sausage, zucchini and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef ragout
directions: Trim visible fat from beef.
Brown in vegetable oil in fry pan. Add mushrooms, wine (1/2 cup water may be substituted) and bouillon cube dissolved in boiling water.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until tender.
Add vegetables and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes longer.
Stir into stew, cook and stir until smoothly thickened and mixture comes to a boil.
Serve with noodles or rice.
Serves 4.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook until golden brown (10 minutes) in 400° oven.

title: hot turkey sandwiches
directions: Heat at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 1/2 hours.
If too soupy, add a little flour.
Spoon onto buns.
Serves about 20. This recipe works well also using chicken, instead of turkey.
Can be made up the day before and refrigerated until ready to bake. Using a crock-pot works well, also.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Make a dark roux with oil and flour.
Boil chicken in 2 quarts water, and debone.
Boil some of the grease out of the sausage, drain and slice into small pieces.
In dark roux, saute onions, celery, and bell pepper.
Add water in which chicken was boiled.
Add bay leaves, salt, pepper, and other seasonings to taste.
Add chicken pieces and sausage.
Simmer about 1 hour. Remove bay leaves.
Serve in soup bowls over a large spoonful of rice.
If desired, sprinkle prepared gumbo file (1/2 tsp.) over top.
Do not cook file in pot.

title: quick cherry cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese and add sugar, flour and salt.
Blend well; add remaining ingredients except pie filling and crackers. Crush graham crackers on bottom of 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Pour cream cheese mix over crackers.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack.
Spread with pie filling and chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Baking time:
50 to 60 minutes.

title: oreo icebox dessert
directions: Crumble cookies and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, cream together peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add 10x sugar and milk; beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture over cookie crumbs.
If desired, top with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm.
To serve, place in refrigerator approximately 10 minutes prior to serving time.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, chiles, olives, garlic powder and hot sauce. Stir well. Spread 1/4 c. cream cheese mixture on each tortilla. Top with chicken slice. Roll Tortillas and wrap tightly in plastic. Chill 2 hours. Slice into 1 inch rounds.

title: zucchini with stewed tomatoes
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add zucchini.
Cook, stirring, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Stir until hot.

title: savory broccoli and brussels sprouts
directions: Trim and cut broccoli into florets.
Trim Brussels sprouts, removing yellow leaves.
Either steam vegetables or drop into boiling salted water.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Repeat with carrots, cooking only 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Meanwhile, melt butter.
Stir in lemon juice, marjoram, basil, salt and black pepper.
Pour over hot vegetables and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Place chicken in pot with enough water to cover it completely. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until done.
Remove chicken from broth.
Add noodles to broth.
You may need to add additional water so the noodles will cook properly, but not too much.
While noodles are cooking, debone chicken and tear or cut into bite size pieces.
Add chicken to noodles; finish cooking noodles to desired doneness.
This should be thick.

title: chicken oriental(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soy sauce, garlic, ginger, oil, salt, pepper and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
If time allows, marinate all day in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix milk and persimmons; squeeze with your hand and run through a colander or sifter.
If using the 1 cup persimmon pulp, omit milk.
Mix pulp with remaining ingredients and pour into iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable skillet
directions: Preparation: Heat 4 tablespoons oil in large heavy skillet. Add eggplant. Fry, turning once or twice, until lightly browned and tender. Remove. Set aside.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold whipped topping into mixture.
Pour into prepared crusts.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake in 350° oven until heated through. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers of choice.

title: poulet chassour
directions: Peel tomatoes after dropping them for 30 seconds in boiling water; cut in halves and press to remove seeds and cut in squares one-inch size.
Peel and finely chop the shallots.
Tie together the aromatic herbs with cooking string.
Clean the mushrooms; cut them in 4. Heat oil and butter in a thick bottom stewpan; fry the chicken pieces until golden on all sides, then remove from skillet and drain on a plate.
Add shallots and mushrooms in the pan; fry lightly, then sprinkle with the flour.
Mix well; pour wine and water.
Return the chicken pieces inside the pan; add tomatoes, aromatic herbs, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly; simmer 40 minutes on low heat.
Sauteed potatoes or simply steamed potatoes, sprinkled with tarragon, will go nicely with this.
Serve with a dry white wine.

title: best broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli heads close, wash and drain.
Toss together with onion, grapes, and crumbled bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, and sugar separately, then pour over the rest of the salad.
Mix all together and chill before serving.
The best way to eat broccoli!

title: best carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured pan, 10 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together the pumpkin, eggs, spice and sugar.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix and nuts.
Drizzle with butter over cake.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: baked eggs
directions: Put butter into baking dish that is at least 2 inches deep. Warm dish long enough to melt butter.
Cool dish so eggs will not set, but butter will remain liquid.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over butter.
Break eggs in 4 separate places far enough apart so they will not run into each other.
Put dashes of Tabasco and Worcestershire in center of each yolk.
Spoon ketchup over yolks. Pour in cream.
Bake at 350° until eggs are set.
Serve each egg on slice of buttered toast.

title: play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in cooking pot.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Mixture stirs up fast.
Remove from heat immediately and remove from pot quickly.
It will stick! Put on waxed paper to cool.
Store in covered container or plastic bag that seals well.

title: spice tea
directions: Thoroughly clean your percolator.
Place sugar and spices in a basket (liquids in bottom).
Perk or combine all in a saucepan. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Transfer to server.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Saut mushrooms in oleo.
Add rice and oregano.
Stir 5 minutes.
Slice onions with tops.
Put all in greased casserole. Add bouillon and water.
Bake covered for 45 minutes at 450°. Saut pineapple in oleo and serve over rice.

title: crock-pot down south barbecue
directions: Put half of the onions in bottom of crock-pot, then add meat and other ingredients with remaining onions on top.
Cover and cook overnight or 8 to 12 hours on low.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Cut into very small pieces. Dice potatoes and onions. Combine chicken, ground beef, potatoes, onions, corn, tomato paste, catsup, margarine and Worcestershire sauce with 2 cups water in which chicken has been cooked. Simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: salmon party loaf
directions: Flake salmon.
Remove skin and bone.
Combine salmon with next 6 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill 2 hours.
Shape salmon mixture in 8 x 2-inch log.
Combine parsley and pecans.
Roll salmon log in mixture.
Chill well.
Serve with crackers.

title: nana's triple fruit salad
directions: Add water to the reserved pineapple juice to make 1 cup. Bring to a boil.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, oil, and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Combine dry ingredients, except walnuts.
Add alternately with apple mixture to egg mixture.
Finally, add walnuts.
Pour into greased 9 inch x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Combine powdered sugar, lemon juice, vanilla, and corn syrup. Drizzle over cooled cake.

title: butter dips
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch, remove butter from oven when melted.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Cook noodles and rinse. Alternate noodles, sauces and cheeses.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: grandma's chocolate dumpling pie(50 years or older)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and vanilla.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
While the mixture is heating, take flour, oil and water and make a few dumplings.

title: orange yogurt scones
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, 1/3 cup sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut in butter until mixture forms fine crumbs. Mix yogurt, orange peel and juice together and add to flour mixture. Stir just until evenly moistened. Mound dough on an oiled 12 x 15-inch baking sheet. With well-floured hands, pat mound into an even 9-inch round. With a floured knife, cut through the dough to make 8 wedges; leave in place on pan. Sprinkle with the remaining 2 teaspoons of sugar. Bake in a 375° oven until golden brown, about 25 minutes. Serve hot or slide onto a rack and let cool until warm. Cut into wedges. Serve with orange marmalade or a favorite fruit preserves. Serves 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order listed in 2-quart casserole pan.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Serve without tossing.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with 2 cups fruit juice.
Add peaches, pineapple and bananas.
Chill and serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and beat until smooth.
Drop by tablespoons into deep hot grease.
Use plenty of grease.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain and serve hot.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix together powdered sugar and cornstarch. Add milk and egg yolks and cook slowly until thick.
Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter. Pour into cooled 9 or 10-inch baked crust. Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham pie
directions: Mix ingredients (except biscuits) and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Add biscuits on top and bake until biscuits are brown (about 12 minutes).

title: mommom sarah's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, mix the butter and chocolate until well blended.
Beat in the sugar, then beat in the eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla extract.
Add the dry ingredients; stir to form a batter.
Stir in the walnuts.
Pour the batter into the prepared pan; spread the batter out evenly.
Bake brownies for 25 minutes, or until just set.
Cool brownies completely in pan on rack.
Cut into 1 3/4 x 2 1/4-inch rectangles. Remove from pan with a metal spatula to avoid sticking and breaking.
Store in an airtight tin.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with a layer of whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk.
After beaten, add Cool Whip. Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Layer more crackers.
Pour over remaining mixture.
Top with layer of crackers.

title: orange cream cheese mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; chill until white.
Combine cream cheese, cold water, mayonnaise, sugar and nuts in blender. Add to thickened gelatin.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart mold.
Chill.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in onion, green pepper and dried beef.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot. Serve crackers of your choice.

title: strawberry snow
directions: Mix everything together, except cake. Break cake into bite size pieces in a large bowl. Fold liquid ingredients into cake pieces with your hands gently. Thaw strawberries and pour over the mixture. Mix gently with hands. Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all these ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: jamaican airplane cake
directions: Mix in a bowl; pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: aunt brenda's brownies
directions: *I use self-rising flour and omit baking powder and salt.

title: oh! so good chicken
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions.
Add salsa and chilies. Cook until thick, about 5 minutes. Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture.
In a 10-inch square pan, which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, layer the chicken or turkey.
Pour salsa mixture on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Mix reserved salsa, rice and sour cream.
Place on top of meat.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: ham dip
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, milk and mustard.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes a great dip for crackers, or use as a sandwich spread.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well.
Place on large sheet of aluminum foil; flatten.
Arrange ham slices on beef.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Roll up using foil.
Seal meat.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter with both sugars.
Add eggs.
Heat to boil orange juice, dates and baking soda.
Cool.
Add when cool to butter mixture.
Add flour, spices and prepared fruit.
Fruit needs to be chopped and coated with flour.
Add pecans.
Batter will be stiff. Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool before removing.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: maple cream coffee treats
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, combine brown sugar, nuts, syrup and 1/4 cup margarine; spread evenly into bottom of pan.

title: tang salad
directions: Mix together and chill until ready to serve.

title: creole seasoning
directions: Combine all the ingredients and stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour into a large glass jar.

title: spicy breadsticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Press or roll dough into rectangle, 24 x 12-inch.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle evenly over dough. Gently press herb mixture into dough. Cut dough into 24 strips, 12 x 1-inch.
Place strips 1/2-inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: angel food cherry cheese cake
directions: Put cake pieces in a large casserole
dish. Add the crushed pineapple and juice.

Mix cream cheese and eagle brand milk with electirc mixer until smooth. Fold in cool whip. Put three large serving spoons of this into cake pieces. Mix and smooth down into the casserole dish. Pour remainder of cream cheese mixture over cake pieces and smooth out. Add cherry pie filling on top and spread. Add pecans. Put in refrigerator for at least four hours. Over night is better.

title: baked ice cream pie(makes one 9-inch pie.)
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in cream of tartar and sugar until meringue is stiff.
Add vanilla.
Pack ice cream firmly in cooled pastry shell.
Spread meringue over entire surface so that it touches edges of pastry. Bake at 450° for 3 minutes, or until meringue is delicately brown. Serve at once.

title: broccoli medley
directions: Wash and separate broccoli into flowerets and bite size pieces.
Cut up onions.
Combine broccoli and onions in Pyrex dish, then combine mayonnaise, vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix until mixture is smooth.
Pour over broccoli; let sit overnight or 12 hours.
Before serving, fry bacon.
Crumble bacon over mixture.
Sprinkle raisins and almonds.

title: fingerman bread sticks
directions: Cut loaves into halves lengthwise.
Cut each half into 8 equal pieces, using sharp knife or scissors.
Pierce each piece 2 to 3 times with a fork to remove air bubbles.
Place melted butter in shallow dish.
Combine cheese and seasoning on a plate; put onion on separate plate.
Roll each piece of dough into an 8-inch log. Roll each log in butter, then in desired topping.
On a cookie sheet, bake in preheated oven at 350° until browned, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm with salsa, cheese or desired topping.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, salt and soda. Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and oatmeal.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop on greased pan. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; mix well.
Mix flour and spices.
Add to first mixture. Stir in zucchini.
Pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake about 40 to 45 minutes until done at 325°.

title: raspberry cooler
directions: Dissolve drink powder and sugar in 4 cups water.
Add juices. Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of buttered pan. Sprinkle onion soup mix on top. Place chicken breast on rice. Spoon chicken soup on top of chicken. Add boiling water. Bake, uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup oleo. Mix until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in thin strips; dredge with flour.
Brown quickly in skillet in half the butter.
Remove the meat; add remaining butter.
Add onions and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Add meat with salt and pepper.
Add tomato juice, wine and water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Season to taste; stir in sour cream and serve.
Excellent with wild rice.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (or may microwave on medium for 10 minutes).

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening gradually.
Add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chilled strawberry cake dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until it begins to thicken, then fold in whipped cream.
Break up 1/2 of cake into chunks; cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of Jell-O mixture over top.
Break up other 1/2 of cake; form another layer.
Cover with other 1/2 of Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: christmas pound cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar; add vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and milk; beat.
Fold in coconut and cherries. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Place alternate layers of corn and bread crumbs in a greased baking dish with sprinklings of pepper.
Add butter and seasonings to each layer.
Pour over milk and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Brown chops in small amount of grease.
Remove from skillet and drain.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Mix together the salad dressing, milk, dressing mix and pasta in large shallow bowl.
Arrange remaining ingredients over pasta mixture and chill.
Makes 14 cups.

title: grandkid's favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil the macaroni in salted water until just tender.
Drain well.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a large greased bread loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: no egg banana bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions on package.
In separate mixing bowl, soften cream cheese; add confectioners sugar.
Beat and fold in Dream Whip.
Cut angel food cake into thin slices.
Place a layer of cake in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Next add a layer of cream cheese mixture.
Then a layer of cake and spoon remaining cream cheese mixture over cake.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: gold medal plain cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients thoroughly. Add eggs.
Cream with butter and sugar mixture.
Add flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Put mixture in large tube cake pan or 2 small tube pans.
Put in cold oven.
Set oven to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. When done, cool for 5 minutes.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and pepper.
Place in casserole dish in layers of raw, shredded cabbage, hamburger mix, cabbage and hamburger mix.
Pour tomato soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stone soup
directions: Drain beans; put in large kettle.
Add all.
Simmer 30 minutes after final addition and serve.
Good with warm fresh bread!

title: fast fixing fruit and cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; tilt pan to cover bottom.
Put cake mix, eggs and water into pan; stir with a fork or spoon until blended.
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Spoon pie filling into batter; use a fork and fold in batter to create a marbled effect.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: "southern living" grilled vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Cut vegetables in large pieces and put in marinade 30 minutes.
Grill in basket on medium-hot coals (350° to 400°) for about 20 minutes.
Add to marinade and serve hot or chilled.

title: mary's sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, oleo, egg, vanilla and almond extract. Mix in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: tangy tea (russian)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in covered jar.
Use 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons in a cup of hot water (more or less, according to taste).

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix cheeses, Worcestershire, paprika and mustard.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Toast one side of bread slices lightly under a broiler.
Flip the slices over and top the untoasted side with same egg and cheese mixture. Broil 3 to 6 minutes, until puffed and brown.
Serve hot.

title: southern cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble bread crumbs.
Add broth to soften; add eggs.
Add more broth as needed.
Mix in all other ingredients, adding soup last.
Melt 6 tablespoons butter or margarine and mix in well. Bake in greased pan 40 to 50 minutes at 400°.

title: charles' cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in greased pan at 400° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal bars
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and brown sugar, peanut butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Add egg and 1/4 cup milk; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt to mixture until well combined.
Stir in oatmeal and spread evenly in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly, then frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add sour cream and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Drop by heaping spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Wet finger, make hole in center.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 370° 12-15 minutes.

title: salty sticks
directions: *Put sesame on them after you spread the egg yolks.

title: potato salad
directions: Night before (or same day):
Simmer potatoes with skins until they can easily be pierced with a fork (about 40 minutes).
Remove skins and cube.
Add hard-boiled eggs (while warm), chopped, green onions and 3/4 cup Miracle Whip.
Cool thoroughly.

title: steamed mexican rice
directions: Slightly brown rice with margarine, onion, pepper, and soup powder.
When browned, quickly add tomato sauce and water.
let come to a rolling boil.
Then steam on low to med. heat for about 1/2 an hour.

title: meatball recipe
directions: Add enough water to the breadcrumbs to make them solidly mushy.
(I know that's an oxymoron, but it's the best explanation I can think of.)
Add the mushy breadcrumbs to the chopped meat. Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Roll nuts, candy, dates and coconut in 1/2 cup of flour. Cream margarine and sugar; add salt to flour.
Add flour alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add nuts, etc. mixture to batter.
Cook in well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan (or 2 loaf pans) at 250° for 2 1/2 hours or cake shrinks from side of pan.

title: pumpkin pie dip
directions: Place the cream cheese and powdered sugar into the bowl of an electric mixer and beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add the pumpkin, cinnamon and ginger.
Beat until well combined.
Pour the dip into an airtight container.
Cover and chill for at least 8 hours before serving.
To serve, allow the dip to stand at room temperature for about 30 minutes and serve with gingersnaps, apple slices and/or pear slices.
Yield:
3 3/4 cups.

title: special k bars
directions: Heat syrup and sugar together until bubbly. Take off heat. Add peanut butter. Stir well. Add Special K. Mix well. Press into small pan.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugars. Add eggs and mix. Add oatmeal mixture. Add flour, soda, salt and cocoa. Mix well. Add 1 c. chocolate chips. Sprinkle bottom of pan with remaining cup of chocolate chips and pecans. Pour batter over top and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts in orange sauce
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 350°.
Mix orange concentrate, butter and ginger.
Spoon over chicken breasts and bake 30 minutes longer.
When done, sprinkle with cashews.

title: honey garlic wings
directions: Remove wing tip and discard.
Split wing in half.
Place wings, single layer, in large rectangular baking dish.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer in order.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: basic layer cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together, alternately with buttermilk.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Stir together carrots, tomatoes, thyme, marjoram and margarine. Sprinkle Cheez-Its and almonds on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: russian toffee
directions: Put together and stir constantly, especially on bottom while cooking to keep from sticking.
Cook to a 250° temperature or medium hard ball.
Pour into buttered pans.
Nuts or chocolate may be added to a part of it.
Cut into squares and wrap in wax paper.

title: slow-roasted chicken
directions: Thoroughly combine first 6 ingredients and rub mixture into chicken, inside and out. Place in sealable plastic bag and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello and flour.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat, butter and onions.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 10.

title: tricolor pasta with vegetables
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile in large saucepan, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms, zucchini, onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring, until lightly browned and tender.
Stir in tomatoes, oregano and salt.
Cook until tomatoes are just soft.
Add pasta and Parmesan cheese to vegetable mixture in saucepan and toss well.
Serve immediately.

title: pepper rice
directions: Heat oils in a large skillet; add peppers and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in rice and salt.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Fold together yogurt and Cool Whip; blend.
Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, eggs and salt.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce.
Trim with egg slices and olives. Serves 8.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into three 9-inch round floured cake pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with cherry juice and milk.
Beat two minutes.
Add egg whites and beat two more minutes.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Bake in sprayed 9 x 13 pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
In a small bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, cream the butter; add 1/2 cup of the granulated sugar and blend well.
Beat in the flour mixture.
Recipe can be prepared to this point up to a day ahead and refrigerated.
Oil a 9-inch square cake pan and place half the peaches on the bottom. Using a metal pan gives a better texture to this dessert. Sprinkle half the flour mixture over the fruit.
Add the rest of the peaches and then the rest of the flour mixture.
In a small bowl, combine the remaining 1/2 cup of granulated sugar and the brown sugar; sprinkle over all.
Put the almond extract in a 1-cup measure and fill with the boiling water.
Pour over the top of the cobbler, but do not mix.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg and bake for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add pizza sauce, salt and pepper.
Add slices of cheese, two at a time, until melted. Continue until all the cheese is added.
Put on hamburger buns and enjoy.

title: elsie's cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: make-ahead potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, mash, beat in cream cheese, then sour cream, garlic salt and pepper.
Put in buttered shallow casserole or Pyrex dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate up to 2 days.
Bring to room temperature before baking or at least 1/2 hour out of refrigerator to avoid breakage.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 400°,

title: "french-fried" potatoes(pommes frittes au nature)
directions: These are the easiest French fries ever, and the most healthful.
We even leave on the skin, that's where lots of the nutrients are!
Bake at 475° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 servings of 112 calories each.

title: crustless cheesecake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, flour and milk.
Beat in cottage cheese, vanilla and lemon juice.
Turn into prepared large deep spring-form pan heavily buttered and floured.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Flake and chip corned beef.
Add sour cream and onion soup mix.
Mix all together.
Serve on crackers.
Triscuits are good.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
In a mixing bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Mix together melted butter, egg and buttermilk; add to dry ingredients.
Stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.

title: stir-fry squash and snow peas
directions: Combine garlic and butter in 2-quart rectangular or oval shaped microwave dish. Cook on High for 1 minute until butter is melted. Add remaining ingredients and stir to coat with butter. Cover with wax paper and cook on High for 4 minutes, stirring once. Serves 4.

title: layered italian casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in skillet; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, parsley, salt and oregano.
In a greased 8 x 12-inch shallow baking dish, layer the spaghetti, meat sauce, Ricotta and Mozzarella.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese is brown and bubbly.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Bring 2 1/4 cups cold water to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan. Add potatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, over medium heat 15 to 18 minutes or until most of the water is absorbed.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook hamburger meat, pork, shrimp, onions, peppers, carrots, bean sprouts and cabbage together.
Drain well and add egg, m.s.g. and soy sauce.
Spoon ingredients into wonton wrappers.
Roll and deep fry until golden brown.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Split whole package of rolls.
Toast the inside of both sides. Melt oleo.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread mustard mixture on inside of top and bottom of rolls.
Layer ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, melt the oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: agnes' pear relish
directions: Chop pears and vegetables fine.
Mix all together and cook about 5 minutes after it boils.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in the bottom of an unbaked pie shell.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over pecans.
Bake in a 425 degree oven for 10 minutes then lower to 325 degrees and cook another 35 minutes until pie is firm.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Reduce heat to simmer; add pepper, onions, tomatoes, water, macaroni and seasonings.
Cover for 25 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 10 minutes.
Place in a greased dish. Add cheese and bake at 325°
until cheese is melted.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.
Top with 1 cup of sugar frosted flakes mixed with 2 tablespoons of melted butter or margarine.
Can be mixed the day before and cooked later.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter; cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Divide in half and roll in powdered sugar.
Roll in wax paper.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: shrimp or deviled ham dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill and serve with assorted crackers.

title: alaskan cod
directions: In a skillet or electric pan, melt butter and saute garlic with about 1 teaspoon to 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Cut cod into serving size pieces and place in pan.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper. Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Turn cod over and simmer a few more minutes (5 to 7 minutes).
(When I take the cod out and arrange on dish, I place freshly sliced lemon on top of each one and a sprig of parsley.) Serve with fried rice, fresh garden salad and hot bread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Use just the tender part of the Broccoli. Chop fine, mix in rest of ingredients. Let set overnight.

title: slush
directions: Mix jello, Kool-Aid, sugar and boiling water together.
Add frozen lemonade, pineapple juice and 10 to 14 cups of water.
Stir well.
Freeze for 8 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken a la ritz
directions: Place chicken pieces in 15-inch casserole. Blend sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Cover chicken pieces.
Top with crushed crackers and 1/2 cup butter, melted.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 6 week bran muffin
directions: Mix cereal with sugar, flour, soda and salt in very large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening or oil, honey and buttermilk.
Store in covered container in icebox and use as desired.
To bake,
fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp salad and shells
directions: Combine all ingredients except shells.
Mix lightly with fork. If shrimp are 1 to 1 1/2 in size, cut in half.
Fill pasta shells with small spoon.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: joyce's kentucky pie
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into 8-inch pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut the eggs in half. Mix all the ingredients with the egg yolks. Then fill the egg whites with the mixture.

title: crisscross peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Add peanut butter, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls and flatten with fork to make crisscross design.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Combine pumpkin and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting when cool.

title: nut meringues
directions: Place all ingredients, except nuts, in mixer bowl and beat on high for 12 minutes or more.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in a slow oven (300°) until a delicate brown.
Store in an airtight container.

title: microwave italian meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into 1 1/2-inch meat balls (makes about 20).
Arrange in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish; heat 10 to 12 minutes, draining liquid and rearranging meat balls once. Yields 4 servings.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss.
Place in a well greased 9 by 13-inch casserole dish.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cream cheese-cherry sandwiches
directions: Blend cream cheese and cherries; add nuts.
Spread on bread, cut to small sandwich size.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Combine tomato, green pepper, onion and pickles.
Combine mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Layer third of corn bread, top with third of vegetables, third of mayonnaise and top with third of bacon.
Repeat layers, ending with the last third of bacon.
Cover and chill at least two hours.
(I use a round glass salad bowl as the layers are so pretty.)

title: peaches-n-cream pie
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Combine the first 7 ingredients in bowl and beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into pan.
Place peaches over batter.
Combine in bowl the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved peach juice.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon to within 1-inch of edge of batter.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over cream cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas pinto beans
directions: Heat water and beans to boiling in 3-quart saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: skillet burgers
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place mixture 1/2 inch deep in skillet or baking pan or dish.
Cook on top of stove 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.
Place thinly sliced cheese on top of mixture and another 1/2 inch of hamburger.
Cook until most of cheese is melted.
Place under broiler 5 or 10 minutes.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs, oil, and pie filling.
Add just enough water (very little) to make batter the right consistency.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: In heavy kettle, heat oil and add minced garlic.
Mince parsley and add.
Stir until wilted.
Add clam juice, tomato juice, stewed tomatoes, basil and wine.
When boiling, add seafood.
Cook until seafood is done, about 15 to 20 minutes at reduced heat.
Clams should have opened and the shrimp and crab should be pink.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Lightly brown meat in fat in large electric skillet at 350°. Sprinkle 1/2 of spaghetti mixture over meat.
Spread cottage cheese over meat.
Then arrange uncooked noodles in layer. Sprinkle remaining spaghetti sauce mix, basil, parsley flakes and salt. Add tomatoes with liquid.
Be sure all is moistened.
Cover tightly.
Set temperature at 200° or 225°.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes or until noodles are done.
Disconnect cord.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: dorothy lynch homestyle salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for 1 minute or until smooth. Serve.

title: unbelievable cake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; pour over shortening, sugar and salt.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Add eggs, yeast and lemon rind.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Stir in sweet potatoes; add milk gradually to form soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead lightly.
Roll or pat 1/2 inch thick; cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in large, greased and floured cookie sheet/jelly roll pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: banana bars
directions: In large bowl, beat banana, margarine, sugars and flavorings at high speed.
If energetic, do by hand.
Beat in egg, then add flour mixture.
Mix well together.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir.
Combine egg and milk.
Dip fillets in egg mixture, then dredge in flour.
Arrange in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Drizzle with butter, sprinkle almonds over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except mayonnaise, then add about 2 tablespoons mayonnaise to ingredients.
Mix well.
Nice fruit salad.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Wash meat.
Dip in flour, then eggs, then bread crumbs mixed with Parmesan and/or other seasonings.
Fry in butter 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: ora's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour in 3 medium size loaf pans or 3 greased and floured coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: bistra's bulgarian meatball soup
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, paprika, and savory.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Form meat into 1 inch balls, then roll in flour.
Combine water, bouillon cubes, 1 tsp. salt. 1 tsp. pepper, green onions, green pepper, carrots and tomatoes in a large kettle.
Cover, bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add meatballs, cover and bring to a boil again.
Reduce heat and simmer another 20 minutes.
Add chiles and simmer uncovered for 40 minutes or until rice is done. Add parsley during last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Just before serving beat egg with lemon juice.
Stir in 1-2 Tbsp. hot soup into egg/lemon mixture, pour into soup.
Heat and stir until soup slightly thickens, but do not boil.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs, flour and vanilla and mix well. Then stir in gumdrops and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Dot with cut up gumdrops, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yield: 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix these two ingredients together and pack down in a 9 x 12 cake pan.

title: best ever turkey casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Place in 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with Veg-All.
Add cheese soup, undiluted, and cover with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes; then uncovered for 15 minutes to brown Tots.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Heat sour cream, soup, chilies, onions and chicken.
Layer in casserole dish, starting with corn chips, then heated chicken mix and then cheese.
Layer twice.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugars together, then add butter and pecans. Pinch the biscuits up into mixture and mix thoroughly.
Put in an ungreased Bundt pan.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and sour cream.
Let thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Make layers
of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding, ending with pudding. Sprinkle wafer crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk over low heat. Blend cream cheese and sugar with mixer; add rest of milk to cream cheese and sugar and mix well.
Add chocolate mixture to cream cheese mixture; mix until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip, using mixer. Pour into pie shell.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: cote pork pie
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Add 1 cup water and cook until pink is gone.
Add 2/3 cup fine dry bread crumbs.
Bake about 50 or 60 minutes (until crust is cooked) as a 2 crust pie at 400°.

title: cool whip lemon pie
directions: Mix together lemon juice and milk.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple.
Pour into the pie crusts and chill.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces and place in baking dish. Add soup and flour to broth and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Put grated eggs on top of this.
Add a pie crust and cook for 40 minutes at 350 degrees or until golden brown.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except yeast and sugar together. Mix sugar and yeast in small bowl; set aside. Heat buttermilk in small pot until warm; add yeast, sugar, and oil. Mix well and add to dry ingredients. Knead well. Make into biscuits and let rise. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add carrots, oil, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until moistened.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Melt shortening and margarine in microwave.
Add lukewarm water.
Add rest of ingredients (only 1/2 flour).
Add rest to consistency.
Knead and raise 1 hour.
Punch down and make rolls, raise again.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli in cheese puff
directions: Cook broccoli until barely tender.
Put in buttered 8-inch baking dish.
Make White Sauce; add cheese.
Beat egg yolks, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Add to White Sauce.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into sauce.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sauce for fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over low heat. Stir constantly until thickens. Cool pour over fruit.

title: women's city club salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and onion in mixing bowl.
Wet mixture with small amount of vinegar.
With beater set at low speed, add oil and vinegar alternately, adding more oil each time than vinegar, reserving a bit of vinegar.
Add celery seed with the last of the vinegar.
Mixture should be thick and stable.
Store in covered jars and refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 pints.

title: sausage-egg bake
directions: Brown sausage; drain and reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk and drippings.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in sausage and hard-boiled eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May be served with butter and topped with syrup, if desired.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, drain and cool.
Peel, core and thinly slice apples into rings.
Arranges half of apples and half of potatoes slices in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish, sprinkle with half the brown sugar mixture and dot evenly with half of margarine.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, serve warm.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Blend flour, salt, sugar, chili powder and Tabasco.
Brown onion and celery in oil slowly.
Add the blended ingredients to onions and celery.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomatoes, peas, vinegar and shrimp.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cream of tartar.
Drop 22 Ritz crackers in mixture; do not stir, or you will break crackers.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and put butter over the top.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°; reduce temperature to 325° or 350° and bake an additional 25 minutes.
Tastes like apple pie.

title: bacon and shell-roni
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; pour off part of fat.
Add onion and tomato sauce.
Simmer until thickened, adding garlic salt to taste.
Sauce should taste a little salty.
Cook shells as per instructions on box; add sauce to shells.
Serve with garlic bread and a salad.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries, orange, apple and nuts on coarse blade of food chopper.
Add crushed pineapple, coconut flakes and sugar. Mix well.
Make 24 hours before serving.

title: golden glow noodles
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Mix in milk, salt and flour.
Knead dough in bowl to form a ball until very smooth, about 1 minute. Cover; let rest 30 minutes.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll each part on floured surface.
Keep remaining dough covered until ready to roll.
Cut into long strips, about 3 inches wide.
Let stand about 15 minutes, then cut into narrow strips about 1/4-inch wide. Dry for at least 1 hour.
Cook in 3 quarts salted water (1 tablespoon salt) or in chicken broth.
Serves 4.

title: punch
directions: Heat water and sugar together to dissolve.
Add rest of ingredients; fill gallon jug with water and let set 7 to 8 hours before serving.
Or it's better to freeze and serve as a mush.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put a layer of chocolate chips, layer of coconut, another layer of chocolate chips, and another layer of coconut.
Pour milk over this and bake at 350° until done.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Mix shrimp, cheeses, onions and pimento in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Boil together for 2 minutes the sugar, milk, butter, cocoa and salt. Wait until it starts a rolling boil. Take off stove and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop from spoon on wax paper. Makes about 35 to 40 cookies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup oleo and Velveeta cheese together.
Mix with vegetables.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and 1/4 cup butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef cubes in margarine.
Add mushrooms.
Add flour and soup mix; stir.
Add milk and water.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour. Add sour cream; reheat 10 minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: hot cheese and crab dip
directions: Combine cheese and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in crabmeat and wine. Cook until heated.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 2 cups.

title: beef-stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Mix
first
5 ingredients, 2 teaspoons of salt and dash of pepper.
Cut core out of cabbage to depth of 3-inches.
Put cabbage in	a
large
kettle
of boiling water over high heat. With tongs,
remove
about 20 leaves as they wilt.	Let leaves stand
until
cool.
Chop	remaining
cabbage.
Put
half	of chopped cabbage
in bottom of large kettle.
Put a spoonful of meat mixture
in
center
of each leaf.
Roll up, tucking ends under cabbage
rolls.
Put	on
top of cabbage in kettle.
Top with
remaining
cabbage, sauerkraut, tomato sauce and butter. Salt and
pepper
to
taste.
Add
boiling	water.	Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: bologna casserole or stew
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Let this simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over warm biscuits.
(I cook this in my electric frypan.)

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape small portions into rolls. Wrap in waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator until hard or overnight. Slice in thin slices.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: shrimp cheese appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese and finely chopped green onions.
Spread in a quiche dish.
Top with finely chopped shrimp.
Cover with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat. Make a paste of the cocoa and food coloring, then add to mixture. Add buttermilk, alternating with flour and salt. Beat until smooth. Add vanilla.
Dissolve soda in vinegar, then add and mix well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased and floured cake pans.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add soups, Ro-Tel and chili powder.
Dip tortillas in broth chicken was cooked in to soften.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, baking soda and salt well.
Then add milk, eggs, bacon grease and creamed corn.
Mix well.

title: t. v. snacks
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and pour over the remaining ingredients.
Cook at 200° for 2 hours.
Turn every 15 minutes.

title: mexican potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and chop into bite size pieces.
Chop onion into small pieces.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Melt margarine in soup pot and add onions and cook slightly.
Add potatoes and fry briefly.
Add tomatoes and cook briefly.
Cover all with boiling water and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add 1 small can chopped chilies.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add 2 pounds small cubed cheese.
Allow to melt and serve with warm tortillas.

title: noodle candy
directions: Over low heat, melt the chocolate and butterscotch morsels. Add the noodles and peanuts.
Spoon out onto waxed paper or foil. Place in refrigerator until set up.
Serve.

title: mexican dressing
directions: Mix peppers and onion in hot broth; let stand until everything else is ready.
Beat eggs well and mix in milk.
Pour in cornbread mix and mix well.
Add broth and chicken to mix.
Add tomatoes. Pour in a microwavable dish and cook about 6 to 8 minutes.
If mix is dry, add a small amount of broth.
Top with picante sauce.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavored dressing cornbread mix

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 8 x 8 pan. Spread croutons on bottom of pan. Pour shredded cheese over croutons. Combine eggs, milk, mustard, salt, onion powder and pepper; mix well and pour over cheese and croutons. Cook and crumble bacon. Sprinkle over top. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: single pie crust #2
directions: Combine flour and salt. Cut Crisco or butter in with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture has lumps no larger than peas and is evenly coarse.
Sprinkle with water, one tablespoon at a time, blending with a fork until mixture holds shape of ball. Roll out.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt margarine in 1 cup boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once; stir vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each until smooth.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until golden brown and puffy, about 30 minutes. Remove from oven; split.
Cool for about an hour.
Then they may be filled with homemade pudding or Thank You pie filling (canned), chocolate, vanilla or lemon.
Then dust with confectioners sugar. Makes 32 to 36 small puffs.

title: depression dinner (lima beans and sausage)
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain, cover with water and cook until done.
Put in baking dish with brown sugar, mustard and catsup.
Make patties with sausage and put on top. Bake at 375° until sausage is done, turning sausage over once.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot or heavy casserole with a tight lid and cook on low or at 275° for 7 to 9 hours. Add peas and mushrooms the last hour if you wish. Liquid may be thickened with flour or cornstarch.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions and celery in 2 1/2 cups boiling water, covered, until tender.
(Do not drain vegetable water.
This is part of the soup.)
Add bouillon cubes.

title: burnt sugar cake and icing
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder and sift 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar, adding sugar 2 tablespoons at a time.
Cream well.
Add beaten egg yolks, flour and milk.
Add vanilla and burnt sugar syrup alternately.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Use 2 greased and floured round cake pans.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring to boil; boil 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Mixture will bubble and foam up.
Pour over popcorn; place pans in 225° oven and bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour over wax paper and break apart.
Place in tight can or jar.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Spread cranberry sauce in a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine oats, flour and brown sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: fluffy frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold in topping.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts. Freeze and serve.
(If not used the same day, wrap in airtight freezer wrap after pie is frozen.)
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and taco sauce with a hand mixer.
Put into a flat serving dish or platter.
Top with chopped onion, pepper, tomato, olives and then the cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.
Can be prepared the day before serving.

title: yummy salad
directions: Mix jello according to package.
Add rest of desired ingredients.
Mix together and refrigerate to set.

title: meatless but hardy meal
directions: Mix beans and corn with the enchilada sauce.
Fill floured tortillas with the corn/bean mixture and sprinkle with cheese. Roll up and heat.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cake:
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans (that have been greased well) at 325 ° for 35 to 40 minutes until done in middle.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across grain into very thin strips.
In a skillet, over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook beef and garlic until beef is browned.
Add onion.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce; heat to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles.
Preparation time:
10 minutes; cook time:
20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry chewbilees
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Crisco. Set aside.
Chop 1/2 cup nuts coarsely for topping.
Set aside. Chop remaining 1/2 cup finely.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place hash brown potatoes in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and onions and spread over potatoes.
Put cheese on top of mixture.
Crush crackers and place on top and drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together cornstarch, sugar, salt and water in pan.
Cook until clear.
Add strawberry jello.
Pour mixture over 1 quart sliced strawberries in baked pie shell (8-inch).
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with whipped cream.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar and egg; add mustard, butter, vinegar and salt. Bring to a boil and simmer about 5 minutes. Cool. Very good on garden leaf lettuce and green onions.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Grind together clams, celery, onion and pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Stuff shells and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place corned beef in a kettle with cold water.
Add cloves, peppercorns and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Skim surface, then simmer uncovered for 3-4 hours or until meat is fork tender.
Add carrots, potatoes and onions during the last 25 minutes.
Add cabbage during the last 20 minutes.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: spicy applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and applesauce.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: no cook corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Serve at room temperature or cover and refrigerate up to one week.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread nuts on bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan.

After spraying with nonstick spray, place coconut on top of nuts.	Mix cake mix as directed and pour over coconut.	Melt margarine and cream cheese together add powdered sugar and vanilla pour over cake mix. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Mix together the sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and place pan in cold water.
Cool, then stir in vanilla and cream.
Sweeten peaches with sugar to taste. Stir into custard mixture and chill thoroughly in refrigerator. Freeze in churn freezer until very stiff.
Let ripen.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken nachos
directions: In a saucepan mix soup, salsa and chicken; over low heat, heat through (heat 5 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Serve over chips topped with onions and olives.
Serves 6.

title: cheese taco dip
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole, bake at 250 degrees for approximately 25 minutes or until melted, stir occasionally.
Also works well to serve in a small crock pot.
Serve with taco chips.

title: cinnamon 8's
directions: Open can of biscuits; roll into snake shapes, then shape into figure 8 shapes.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Dip figure 8 shapes into butter, then roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Place on baking sheet; bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: st. charles chocolate pies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Gradually add mixture of milk and yolks, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Cook until bubbles and thickens.
Will get thicker when cool.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Stir well.
Pour into baked pastry and top with meringue or whipped topping.
Makes 2 large 9-inch pies.

title: creamy rice with milk
directions: Put rice and water into double boiler.
Add salt and bring to boil and cook over water at medium heat.
When rice has expanded, keep adding milk and stirring occasionally until it has the consistency of custard.
Add 3/4 cups sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
When thoroughly cooked (about 2 hours), pour into bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix together the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla, then add flour, soda and salt, mixing thoroughly.	Add apples and nuts and, again,
mix
thoroughly.
Dough will be very stiff after apples are added.	Bake
in
a tube pan or loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together, except olives.
After tossing, put olives on top and serve.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Roll out dinner rolls flat on baking sheet for crust. Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Cool.

title: lemon pie(century old recipe)
directions: Grate rind and juice of two lemons.
Grate rinds.
Remove seed from juice.
Mix flour and sugar; add milk, egg yolks (well beaten), salt and lemons; cook until thick.
Add butter.
Bake crust.
Pour in filling.
Cover with meringue and bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: vegetable soup for canning
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil for 30 minutes.
Put in clean hoot jars and seal.
Makes approximately 12 quarts.

title: double apple bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, applesauce, oil and egg in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in apple.
Spread batter in ungreased square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean; cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes about 2 dozen bars.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Wash tomatoes, onion and green pepper.
Dice onion and green pepper.
Cut tomatoes in quarters.
Add Crisco and bacon drippings.
Add a little salt and a little crushed red pepper. Let these ingredients cook until done.
Then add cabbage.
Let cook for 20 minutes.
Turn off.
Keep lid on until ready to serve.

title: magic recipes and hints
directions: Rubbing alcohol will make ink pen marks disappear.

title: corn fritters
directions: Form into balls and fry in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: beef stuffed zucchini
directions: Use straight, plump zucchini.
Wash, dry and remove stems. Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp and chop it.
Reserve the shell.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Saute onions for 5 minutes.
Mix in zucchini pulp.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add beef and cook until no pink remains, stirring frequently.
Mix in salt, pepper and oregano.
Stuff shell.
Arrange in an oiled baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining oil and cover with tomato sauce. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yummy sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased, 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple side dish
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, flour, & cheese. Pour into greased dish. Add melted butter to cracker crumbs & spread over pineapple mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix in large bowl and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix 1 hour before baking.
Chill in refrigerator. Can freeze extra.

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix mushroom soup, onion soup mix, ketchup, water and Worcestershire sauce. Add garlic powder and pepper.
Pour mixture over meat.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours in covered roaster or all day in crock-pot.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together for sauce.
Put a layer of Doritos and a layer of the chicken, then a layer of sauce.
