Keep layering until all is used up.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes.
Grated cheese can be put on top just before removing from oven.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Crumble corned beef.
Add to cut up cheese, soup, can of milk and onion.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed potato shells
directions: Cook shells.
Drain and rinse.
Peel potatoes and boil and mash (no milk) with 1 stick butter, add cheese.
Saute onions in 3 sticks butter for 15 minutes.
Spread 1/2 of onions into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place shells stuffed with potato mixture in pan. Cover with remaining onion.
Cover with foil tightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato chips
directions: Toss together sweet potatoes, olive oil and salt in a medium-size bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Spread in a single layer on wire rack on a large baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes, until crisp and edges are curled.
Serve immediately.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries; measure juice and add enough water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Heat half of liquid and add to gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add remaining liquid.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Cut cherries in half and combine with drained pineapple, celery and nuts.
Fold into gelatin and turn into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce and garnish with topping.

title: beef and new pea pods-chinese style
directions: Prepare rice.
Chill meat in freezer until slightly firm.
Cut meat diagonally across the grain into very thin slices.
Mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch, soy sauce, sherry, sugar and salt; pour over meat and mix well.
Snap off tips of fresh snow pea pods; remove strings from pea pods.
Blanch one minute in boiling water. Rinse in cold water and drain well.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Stir in undrained blueberries and pineapple.
Spoon into dish.
Chill until set. Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; beat until smooth.
Spread over congealed layer.
Chill until serving time.

title: corn sticks
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl. Add eggs, milk, and oil, stirring just until moistened.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a simmer. Serve hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine, then combine eggs, sugar, Karo syrup and vanilla with melted margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour mixture into two (2) regular unbaked pie crusts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter. Cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
(You can do this step in the microwave over low heat, also.)
Add sweetened condensed milk and mix well. Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well. Shape 1 tablespoon (use measuring spoon) of dough around each candy, covering completely.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 6 to 8 minutes. Cookies will be soft and appear shiny, but become firm as they cool. DO NOT OVERBAKE.
Remove from cookie sheet. Cool.

title: waikiki dessert
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and 1/4 cup milk; mix well.
Add remaining milk, pineapple and pudding mix; beat only 1 minute. Just before serving, spoon into dessert dishes.
Garnish with cherries.
Yield:
6 servings.
(Dessert may be chilled before serving.)

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 1/3 cup dry mix to 1 cup boiling water.
Makes approximately 4 pounds.
May be stored in 2-pound coffee cans or 5-quart ice cream bucket.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Stir to crumble. Drain.
Spread each slice of bread with margarine and cut into cubes.
Put cubes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with sausage. Top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients. Beat.
Pour over mixture.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Good for Derby Day!

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: Add extra flavor to mashed potatoes by finely chopping onion and adding to potatoes when cooking.
Mash the potatoes as usual, including the onion.

title: one dish sausage meal
directions: Put about 1/4-inch depth of water in skillet.
After cutting it into small round pieces, place sausage in skillet.
Cut potatoes into slices.
Put potatoes on top of sausage.
Salt.
Cut carrots.
Add to potatoes.
Salt.
Cut cabbage.
Add to carrots. Salt.
Cover.
Cook on low to medium heat for about 25 minutes.

title: easy beef tenderloin
directions: Rub tenderloin with vegetable oil.
Do not season until finished roasting.
Cover with foil.
Roast in 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Excellent.

title: chicken scaloppine
directions: Lay each half chicken breast on the work surface, place your hand flat over it, and
cutting parallel to your hand, slice the breast in two.
Heat the oil in a heavy 10-inch skillet over moderately high heat.
In a shallow dish, combine flour, salt, and pepper.
press the chicken into the flour mixture, coating the pieces on both sides.
Shake off any excess flour.
Place half the pieces in the skillet and brown them for 1 minute on each side. Remove the breasts to a warm platter.
Cook the remaining breasts the same way.
Add the butter to the skillet, along with lemon rind, garlic, and parsley.
Add the chicken broth, scraping up any brown bits stuck to the skillet.
Bring the liquid to a boil and let it cook until it thickens slightly.
return the breasts to the pan, along with any accumulated juices, and coat with sauce. Serve with green beans and potatoes or rice.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together.
By hand, roll into 1 1/2-inch balls and brown on all sides.
Roll in flour.
Drop into boiling chicken broth and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on rice.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine oleo, milk and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand for 6 hours.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut together; store covered in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, bake cake mix according to directions.
When completely cool, split layers in halves, making 4 layers.
Ice with coconut mixture.
Refrigerate 3 days.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop, with teaspoons,
on greased cake sheet; press with wet knife. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Dump crushed pineapple in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then layer blueberry pie filling.
Layer the yellow cake mix (dry) over pie filling.
Cut up margarine and place on top of dry cake mix. Cover with chopped pecans.
Bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven. Delicious.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown chopped onions and beef in small amount of bacon grease. Add tomato soup and water, chopped green peppers and olive juice. Let boil until thickens.
Stir. Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cook spaghetti, drain and put in baking dish.
Cut cheese over this. Add meat sauce, over this pour mushroom soup and sliced olives. Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Cook beef and garlic in skillet in hot oil until browned.
Add onion.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: deep fried mozzarella sticks
directions: Cut Mozzarella into sticks.
Beat eggs.
Dip Mozzarella in flour, then dredge in egg mixture.
Roll sticks, finally, in bread crumbs.
Repeat with egg mixture, then bread crumbs.
Freeze sticks in freezer until frozen.

title: georgia style round steak
directions: Pour soup-water and sauce over steak and bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 400°.
Leftover is delicious with spaghetti.

title: chipped beef
directions: Cut roast in bite size pieces.
Layer your roast in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle flour over meat; add salt and pepper.
Continue to layer meat and flour until all are gone.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Add water as needed; cook and stir often.
Cook approximately 4 hours at 350°.
Serve with rice.
Makes approximately 15 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: For stuffing, mix well the Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta cheese and parsley.
Brown ground beef and garlic, then add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Stuff shells, pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 30 shells.

title: orange balls
directions: Melt butter; combine all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: steak in brandy
directions: Rub steak
with salt, pepper and oregano on both sides. In a heavy
skillet melt butter over a low flame and add lemon juice and
Tabasco.
Turn
the
flame
high and add the steak; quickly brown
it
on both sides.
Turn down flame and cook to the desired
point.
Pour
the Worcestershire over the steak; turn out the flame.
Pour brandy in and set aflame.
Allow it to burn until
it goes out.
Serve at once using juices in the skillet as a sauce.

title: german chocolate ice cream
directions: In heavy 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon. Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until thickened. Cook 2 additional minutes. Remove from heat and blend in melted chocolate. Blend a small amount of hot mixture into eggs and return egg mixture to saucepan. Cook 1 minute; do not boil. Remove from heat and add coconut. Cool. Blend in cream and chill. Stir in nuts. Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream butter and soften cream cheese.
Add sugar and egg yolks; mix well.
Continue beating, adding flour and milk alternately.
Fold in egg whites. Grease pans generously.
Bake in 350° preheated oven in tube pan for 1 hour, 3/4 hour for 2 loaf pans.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Stir together Bisquick mix, cheese and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs just until moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
Melt butter in skillet.
Using 2 tablespoons mixture for each round, cook until brown.

title: hamburger treat and salad
directions: Brown beef with small onion; drain and add tomato sauce, olives with juice and raisins.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: oriental rice
directions: Dredge the meat in flour; brown in very small amount of shortening.
Add celery and onions with soy sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add meat.
Mix soup, rice and water; stir well.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all into blender and blend until ice cubes are fine.

title: green rice(yield: 8 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: christmas cheese
directions: Mix Velveeta and cream cheese (use an electric mixer for best results).
Add onion, then mix by hand.
Add Blue cheese, mix by hand.

title: crockpot swiss chicken casserole
directions: Lightly grease crockpot or spray.
Place chicken breasts in bottom of crock and top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk; stir well.
Spoon over cheese and sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted butter over mix.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour together. Add vinegar and water and cook until thick. Add salt and butter. Mix into beets. Simmer until beets are hot.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut up and cook a pack of boneless chicken breast. Use all low fat soups and cheese to cut fat grams and calories. Add all ingredients together. Let simmer for few minutes. Serve with bread and salad. Can be frozen.

title: chinese coleslaw
directions: Toast nuts, seeds and noodles in 350° oven for 15 to 25 minutes or until light brown. Mix together vinegar, oil and sugar and add to slaw mix. Sprinkle slaw mix with seasoning packet that comes with Ramen noodles. Add nut, seed and noodle mixture to slaw right before serving.

title: green and gold casserole
directions: Cook onion in oil until clear-light brown. Cut squash and zucchini into cubes or disks as desired. Into browned onion, stir squash, zucchini, parsley and seasonings.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Microwave Crisco on High power for 45 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Add cocoa; blend. Beat in sugar, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour and nuts.
Cover and refrigerate until firm. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in 10x sugar. Arrange 8 balls 2-inches apart in circle on waxed paper lined plate.
Microwave on Medium power for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cookies are puffed and surface is dry, but cookies are soft when touched.
Cool on waxed paper on countertop.
Before serving, sprinkle with additional sugar, if desired.
Dough can be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: shrimp in garlic sauce
directions: In shallow ovenproof baking dish, stir in shrimp, chili peppers, olive oil and garlic.
Place in a 425° oven and bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until shrimp turns pink, tossing shrimp once or twice.
Remove from heat, sprinkle with paprika and chopped parsley.
Serve with crusty bread for dipping up oil mixture as appetizer or serve over rice as main course.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice.
Add Jell-O.
Stir and let cool. Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
I put this in a Pyrex dish and refrigerate.
Very good.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix
flour,
oleo and 1/2 cup chopped nuts together and pat in 9
x
13-inch
baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: pumpkin bread(servings:  4 loaves)
directions: Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Mix together wet ingredients.
Combine the two.
Fill cans 1/2 full and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Simply combine all ingredients and refrigerate until cool.

title: fried pie crust for 50 pies
directions: Mix flour and Crisco until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients to flour mixture.
Mix into a ball.
Roll out into 4 or 5-inch circles.
Spread with fruit.
Fold over and pinch edges together. Fry in deep fat.
Makes about 50.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: In a small bowl, mix the sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper; blend until smooth.
Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles.
Place in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up side to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: mystery cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses at room temperature.
Combine with onion until well blended.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Line a 1 1/2-pint bowl with plastic wrap.
Turn cheese into bowl.
Pack down firmly and refrigerate one hour.
Turn cheese on to serving tray.
Remove plastic and sprinkle with pecans.
Decorate with parsley and serve with crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cukes, onions and pepper in ice water for 2 hours.
Mix vinegar, sugar and all spices and bring to a boil.
Drain cukes and add small amount to vinegar at a time.
When cukes begin to change color, pack in sterilized jars.
Cover with vinegar and seal tight.

title: chocolate layer pie
directions: Mix together flour, butter and nuts.
Press into 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar and add small Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust. Mix puddings and milk and beat 2 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese topping.
Top with large Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in small pot.
Boil for 1 min.
Pour into a bowl.
Add peanut butter and cereal.
Mix well.
Drop from a tsp. onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: baked fish
directions: Clean fish; wash cavity and dry.
Melt butter or margarine and spread evenly over the bottom of a baking dish.
Combine pepper, salt and paprika.
Sprinkle herb mixture on both sides of fish. Place fish on top of butter.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish is almost done.

title: pinakbet
directions: Clean vegetables.
Put all ingredients into a quart size pot. Cook until done.
Check taste before vegetables are fully cooked and add more fish sauce, if desired.

title: guacamole party dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mash with fork or blend in food blender.
Yields 2 cups.
Wonderful dip for corn chips.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar.
Drain all fruit and cut peaches into small pieces.
Mix all fruit into cream cheese mixture.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish and freeze.
When frozen, cut into squares.
Return to freezer until ready to serve. Can be served frozen or cold.

title: barbecue chicken tenders
directions: Pour barbecue sauce in bowl.
Coat chicken tenders with sauce. Place chicken tenders on cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: easy pie pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Make well in flour.
Add oil and milk.
Stir with fork.
Roll between waxed paper.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: corn and tamale casserole
directions: Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add corn and tamales after cutting the tamales in bite-size pieces.
Use all juice from tamales, even removing the part that sticks to the wrapping.
Mix with seasonings and cook 1 hour at 400° with top on casserole.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium bowl.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In separate bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasonings.
To assemble, spread bean dip on a large, shallow platter.
Top with avocado mixture followed by a layer of sour cream and taco mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake your cornbread at 450° until golden brown.
Cool your cornbread, then crumble into large mixing bowl.
Chop green peppers, green onions, cucumbers and tomatoes; mix all the ingredients together and pour dressing over top; stir well and chill.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Cut up the onion; mix into hamburger.
Mix in the egg.
Add garlic and salt.
Place the hamburger into a pan.
Add mushroom soup on top of the meat loaf.
Now, put the Tater Tots on top of meat loaf also.
Put the meat loaf in the oven for 45 minutes or until desired doneness at 350°.

title: sunday chicken and dressing
directions: Boil fryer; debone and save broth.
Melt margarine and chop onion finely.
Mix chicken, broth, cornbread, margarine and onion. Add can of chicken soup and celery soup.
Stir and add salt and pepper as desired.
Pour into casserole dish; use a dish that will make dressing approximately 1 to 1 1/2 inches thick.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until light brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not grease pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni as directed on box.
Make sauce as follows. Cream flour and margarine together.
Add milk, salt, onion and 1/4 cup grated cheese.

title: butter turkey
directions: Poke holes in turkey using large fork.
Season with seasoning salt and lemon pepper.
Pour melted butter over turkey.
Bake for 2 hours under foil tent, basting occasionally with more butter at 325°.

title: sausage-n-rice
directions: Chop and saute celery, bell pepper and onion with the sausage (crumbled) until tender.
Heat 3 cups of water to boil.
In a casserole dish, add raw rice, soup mix and sauteed mixture; mix well.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes.
Easy to double or triple recipe.
Freezes well.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Boil lasagna noodles.
Chop onions and saute in margarine. Layer margarine-onion mixture, noodles and potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan or large glass lasagna pan.
Bake at 325°, covered, for 1 hour.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.
Serves a crowd.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix the rest.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 300° for about 1 hour; do not overbake.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet and drain well.
Slice cabbage; place on ground beef and cover.
Cook on low heat until cabbage is tender.
Cut Velveeta in small chunks over cabbage; add sour cream.
Cook until cheese melts.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes, or until cheese bubbles.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add cornmeal, beaten egg and milk.
Stir until stiff.
Add melted margarine and beat until light and mixed.
Bake in greased iron frying pan at 425° for about 25 minutes.

title: casserole for two
directions: Cook sausage or ground meat, bell pepper and onion. Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
This can be doubled for 4 to 6 people.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender to form a paste.
Serve over hot pasta (angel hair) or chicken.
Freezes well.

title: chicken pillows
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Combine lemon juice, oil, garlic, oregano and salt.
Mix well.
Add chicken pieces and coat. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple mystery delight
directions: Lightly grease 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour pineapple in baking pan.
In a medium bowl, mix apples, 1/4 cup sugar and lemon juice and layer on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle fruit layers with dry cake mix.
Top with melted butter, 1/4 cup sugar and pecans. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, then cut with knife into serving portions to allow juice to rise to top.
Bake 30 minutes longer. Serve warm or cold.
Serves 12.

title: baked ham
directions: You also need a browning bag and a Cajun needle.

title: fowler special fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add water and well beaten eggs.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Mix well and add all remaining ingredients, except fruits and nuts.
Cut all fruits and nuts in small pieces, except almonds (add those whole).
Bake in 3 layers.

title: spicy crackers
directions: Place crackers in large bowl.
Pour oil over.
Add all dry ingredients and toss.
Let sit 24 hours before serving.
Can be frozen.

title: all to myself cheesecakes
directions: Split cookies, keeping filling on one cookie.
Line muffin pans with foil bake cups.
Place filling covered cookie in bake cups, filling side up.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in eggs just until well mixed.
Spoon cream cheese mixture into baking cups.
Crush remaining cookies and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until set.
Cool. In a small pan, melt chocolate pieces with shortening.
Drizzle over baked cheesecakes.
Cover and chill.

title: dixies
directions: Melt margarine and let cool.
If the margarine is hot it will not work.
Add to margarine the sugars.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs, salt and flour.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts last.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 325°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes and cut into small squares.
You can dust with powdered sugar.
They will be a little soft when you take them out of the oven.
This is a quick treat and I mix with a spoon.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, sugar and pepper.
Cut butter into pieces and work into flour mixture until coarse and crumbly.
Stir in cheese and milk just until dough comes together. Turn onto floured surface.
Knead and pat down to a 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits and bake on greased baking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel dip
directions: Heat until boiling on low to medium heat. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly, being careful not to scorch. Serve with sliced apples, bananas, ice cream, etc.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat; add vanilla.
Add flour gradually, mixing well (batter is stiff).
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: deluxe chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together well and firmly press into a 9-inch pie pan and chill.

title: caramel bananas
directions: You will need 12 ice cream bar sticks.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Then poke holes down through cake with large fork.
Meanwhile, combine milk, sugar and 1 cup coconut in saucepan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute. Carefully spoon over warm cake, pushing coconut into holes. Allow liquid to soak in holes.
Cool completely.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix dates, candy, nuts and coconut with 1/4 cup flour.
Sift remaining dry ingredients, alternately fold them into creamed mix with buttermilk.
Fold in fruit-nut mixture. Spoon into well-greased, floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven; pour on syrup (grated orange and lemon peel, orange and lemon juice and powdered sugar).
Cool on rack.
Then remove from pan.
Wrap in tinfoil and refrigerate for at least 1 day before serving.
Freezes well.

title: party snack
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight bowl.
Makes 5 cups.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in a skillet; cook until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes and next 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Grease pie plate.
Mix ingredients in blender 30 seconds (except reserved coconut).
Pour in pie plate.
Sprinkle reserved coconut on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Leave in oven for 10 more minutes.

title: real english yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except drippings.
Put drippings in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over top of drippings.
Cook at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden.
Serve with gravy over top of slices.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt together. Add milk and oil. Spoon drop into boiling stew. Cook for 15 minutes, turning dumplings often.

title: better brussels sprouts
directions: Cut stem ends from sprouts and remove outer yellow leaves. Cut an X in bottom of each sprout.
Rinse in cold water, drain and pat dry.
Over low heat, melt 2 1/2 tablespoons butter with oil in a large, heavy pot.
Add garlic; cook for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, or just until garlic starts to change color.

title: banana split
directions: Combine crumbs and 6 tablespoons melted butter.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Beat until fluffy.
Spread over graham cracker layer.
Slice bananas lengthwise.
Put on top of other layer.
Spoon crushed pineapple over bananas.
Spread whipped cream on top of bananas. Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Chill 6 hours.
Excellent!

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar and pudding.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour in can and add to the fill line of can.
Freeze according to instructions on freezer.
Any flavor of pudding may be used.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except 7-Up.
When ready to serve, add 7-Up.
If desired, add vodka to taste.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: In bowl, mix well the sour cream, brown sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well, then add nuts (about 1 cup chopped pecans).
Drop 1 teaspoonful per cookie on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs well; add remaining ingredients. Spread into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add syrup, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until pie is firm.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Beat oleo until fluffy; add 1 cup sugar and beat with lemon peel.
Blend in flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk. Add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased and bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and poke holes over all with fork.
Mix juice of 1 lemon and 1/4 cup sugar until dissolved.
Pour over hot loaf and cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Quickly add all remaining liquid ingredients in order.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour in 2 to 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Use metal pans.

title: cherry topped cheesecake
directions: Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
In a large bowl combine remaining cake
mix,
egg and oil (will be crumbly).
Press mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan evenly on bottom and 3/4 up sides of
pan.
In
the
same
bowl
blend
the softened cream cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat for 1 minute
at medium speed.
At low speed, add milk and flavorings. Mix
until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes in a
300° oven until center is firm.
When cool, top with pie filling.
Chill before serving!

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix and Cool Whip together.
Add pineapple, nuts and miniature marshmallows.

title: cake roll
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice together.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt.
Fold in pumpkin. Pour in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with walnuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn out on towel that is sprinkled with walnuts and powdered sugar.
Roll cake and towel together.
Let cool.
Beat smooth the powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Spread over cake.
Roll up and chill.

title: pecan walnut pound cake
directions: Cream
together
sugar	and
butter and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately. Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Beat for 2 minutes on low speed. Fold
in pecans and walnuts.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: bananas foster
directions: Scoop ice cream into 6 balls.
Freeze in 1 1/2-quart serving dish.
Combine butter, sugar, milk and cinnamon.
Heat, uncovered, on High for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring once.
Add banana slices.
Heat on High for 2 minutes, until fruit is warmed.
In 1-cup glass measuring cup, heat rum on High for 20 seconds.
Pour over bananas and flame at once.
Pour over ice cream balls and serve at once.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl except sugar and cinnamon. Pour half the batter into greased and floured Bundt pan. Mix sugar and cinnamon together. Sprinkle over batter and pour remaining batter over top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oven-fried buttermilk chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Combine all ingredients except chicken and buttermilk in pie plate or shallow dish.
Dip chicken in buttermilk, then roll in dry mixture and place on baking sheet.
Bake until juices run clear when chicken is pricked with a fork, about 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: one dish meal
directions: Trim fat from chops and dip in flour; brown in hot fat.
In large casserole dish, place potatoes, carrots, peas, celery and chopped onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; add hot water, top with browned chops and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: glorified chicken bake
directions: In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken, skin side up.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Bake for 20 minutes longer or until chicken is no longer pink and juice is clear.
Stir sauce before serving.

title: citrus green salad
directions: Finely shred enough orange peel to measure 1/4 teaspoon; set aside.
Working over a small bowl, peel and section oranges, reserving orange juice.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and egg yolks.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add milk and flour alternately and beat. Add coconut and beat well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a Bundt or loaf pan, sprayed with Pam, at 300° for approximately 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title: madeline cookies
directions: Melt butter in double boiler and cool to lukewarm.

Add the eggs and sugar. Stir constantly. Remove from heat and beat until thick but light and creamy, incorporating as much air as possible. When cool, sift and add gradually the sifted flour, rum, vanilla and lemon rind. Grease and flour mini pans.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 15 French tea cakes.
Bake shell form cookies at 325° for 8 minutes.

title: cleta's chicken dinner casserole
directions: Layer chicken, beans and macaroni in a baking dish with macaroni on top.
Mix sauce (mayonnaise, flour, milk and Ranch dressing).
Pour sauce over top of macaroni.
Bake casserole at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: venison roast and gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With sharp knife, puncture 4 deep holes in the roast.
Push in each hole 1 cayenne pepper, 1 clove of garlic and green onion.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over roast. Heat oil in a large roasting pan over medium heat on top of stove. Sear the roast on all sides.
Pour wine around the roast.
Cover roast and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in oven.
Gravy will form from meat juices and the wine.

title: corn relish
directions: Grind onions, cucumbers, tomatoes and peppers.	Boil all ingredients for 40 minutes.
Dissolve 1 1/4 tablespoon flour in a little water.
Add to mixture.
Boil 10 minutes longer.
Place in jars and seal.
Makes about 13 pints.

title: guacamole 1
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender until blended well, chill and enjoy with Southwestern food or chips.
tags: drops of green food coloring to add color

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In large kettle, cook onion in margarine until tender; stir in flour.
Gradually stir in water then broccoli, bouillon and Worcestershire.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and broccoli is tender, about 10 minutes.
Add cheese and cream. Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot (do not boil). Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and egg.
Add dry ingredients and milk. Add nuts.
Allow to rise 1/2 hour, then bake.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine meats, cracker crumbs, eggs and milk.
Put into meat loaf pan.
Mix vinegar, water, brown sugar and mustard.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: simple salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with chips. For a thinner salsa put in blender and blend to desired consistency.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and blend.
Chill dough at least one hour.
Drop teaspoon size balls onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Dip small glass in sugar and press into each mound.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes approximately 100 cookies.

title: my special cabbage and pea casserole
directions: In a
large skillet, heat butter, water, sugar and spices. Add cabbage and peas. Cover and steam over high heat until cabbage is crisp-tender (5 minutes), stirring only once.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in an ungreased oblong baking dish and cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut cherries and pineapple into small pieces.
Mix together well.
Add brown sugar and butter or margarine.
Mix well.
Beat eggs lightly with fork and add to mixture.
Add vanilla, buttermilk and bourbon.
Mix well.
Combine baking soda, baking powder, allspice and nutmeg in small bowl.
Add to mixture.
Add raisins and pecans and mix well.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 30 or 40 minutes.
With teaspoon drop on ungreased baking sheets with cookies not touching one another.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Place in container and cover.
When all are baked, leave tightly covered until next day, then put in airtight container and freeze until Christmas.

title: swiss tuna quiche
directions: Pierce
pastry thoroughly with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
In
bowl
toss
together
tuna,
cheese
and onions. Spoon into pastry.
In small bowl beat together eggs, mayonnaise and milk.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown and inserted knife comes out clean. Makes 4 large servings.
Delightful
luncheon or light supper with salad and fruit.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix together and make into meat balls the first 7 ingredients. Set aside.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Put all together in bowl and mix for 4 minutes.
Grease and sugar an angel food cake pan.
Bake 1 hr. at 350°.

title: carne-asada(mexican steak marinade)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Rinse steak and place in marinade overnight.
Grill.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: Combine spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise and soup seasoning in blender.
Pour mixture into red cabbage shell and surround with vegetable sticks.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine green beans and soup.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Top with onions.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: salmon supreme casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole; top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: amish friendship cake
directions: Day 1:
Pour starter into glass gallon jar and add 1 can peaches and juice (cut each slice into 4 pieces).
Add 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir, cover jar loosely and keep at room temperature. Stir every day for 10 days.
It may take several days for sugar to dissolve.

title: janytra's favorite biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir with fork or mix with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk until dough leaves side of bowl (dough will be sticky).
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 10 times.
Roll or pat 1/2-inch thick. Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown (10 to 12 minutes). Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Yields 1 dozen biscuits.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients all together and pat into 11 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients together and pour on cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots.
While boiling carrots, mince onion and make cracker crumbs.
Melt butter.
Mash carrots; save some of the juice, about 1 1/2 to 2 cups.
Mix all of the ingredients and the grated cheese together. Juice should be added, 1/2 cup at a time, to moisten.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle dried parsley on top.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and lard.
Stir in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk until well blended.
Stir in extract.
Drop on greased cookie sheet in mounds of 2 tablespoons each, about 2 inches apart.
Leave them well-rounded.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar and bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 12 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.
Good iced with the following Butter Frosting.

title: sunday meat loaf
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Add ground beef; mix until blended.
Shape into an 8 x 4-inch loaf and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salt crystal garden
directions: In a glass or plastic bowl, put in pieces of coal or whatever. Over these, pour 2 tablespoons water, 2 tablespoons salt and 2 tablespoons bluing.
The next morning, add 2 tablespoons salt.
On the third morning, pour in the bottom of the bowl, 2 more tablespoons each of salt, water and bluing, then add a few drops of coloring to each piece.
By this time, a beautiful flower-like growth should have appeared.
A free circulation of air is necessary.
These formations will develop better where the air is dry.
It may be necessary to add 2 tablespoons of household ammonia to aid growth.
To keep it growing, just add more bluing, salt and water from time to time.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix as listed.
Almonds and potato chip topping optional. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
May mix ahead of time.

title: jimmy's wonderful donuts(from my cousin, "jimmy the barber")
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Open biscuit package and separate dough into slices (as directions tell you).
Cut small hole in middle of dough and save for later.
When oil is heated, fry up doughnuts and little middle pieces until golden brown (this should only take a minute or two) and drain on paper towel.
Put some confectioners sugar in small brown bag and coat warm doughnuts and middles. Enjoy!

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute onions and margarine in skillet.
Add ground round and brown; drain fat (usually this is not needed).
Add rest of the ingredients and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook carrots for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook for another 4 minutes.
Add soup and sour cream.
Set aside.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: goo-loush
directions: Dice onion and green pepper. Boil macaroni until done.
Drain all excess water.

Fry hamburger meat. Drain grease off and mix in with the macaroni, adding onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce. After all ingredients have been added, simmer for 15 minutes. Add grated cheese.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and water; cook until thick.
Beat the egg yolks; add slowly to the thickened, cooked ingredients.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add the butter, lemon juice and grated rind.
Pour into a baked pie crust.
Beat the egg whites.
Add vanilla and cream of tartar; beat until soft peaks form.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar; beat until stiff peaks form.
Put on filling, being careful to seal the meringue onto the edge of crust to prevent shrinking and weeping.
Bake at 350° until meringue is lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: whole wheat honey bran bread
directions: Put 1 medium sized potato and water in which it has been cooked through a sieve into a large bowl.
This should measure 1 1/2 cups. Add cooking oil, honey and salt to potato water.
Cool to lukewarm and add the yeast which has been softened in the lukewarm water. Stir well to mix.
Then stir in the flours and bran which have been combined.
Mix well.

title: egg bread for dinner rolls
directions: In a small bowl or glass 2-cup measuring cup, sprinkle the yeast over the warm water and stir to dissolve and add 2 teaspoons of the sugar to make the yeast work.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl or mixing machine with dough hook put 4 1/4 cups bread flour, balance of the sugar and the salt and stir together.
Beat the eggs lightly, add the oil and set aside.
When the yeast has worked, add it to the flour mixture in the bowl and mix, then add the eggs and oil and mix until well blended.
Mix for 5 minutes in a machine or knead for 10 minutes by hand.
This is a soft dough.

title: garbage dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with crackers.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Place bran flakes, milk, egg and oil in mixing bowl and beat well.
Let sit for about 1 minute.
Add sifted dry ingredients to the bran flakes mixture until well moistened.
Add blueberries.
Fill muffin pans. Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: camp-out mix
directions: In 2-gallon storage bag, combine Kellogg's Crispix cereal, crackers and pretzels. Pour oil over cereal mixture.
Close bag and gently toss cereal mixture until well coated.
Add salad dressing mix and close bag.
Gently toss cereal mixture until coated well.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 13 cups.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pear salad
directions: Heat pear juice and dissolve lemon jello in it.
Cut cream cheese into jello mixture and beat with wire whisk.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Fold in chopped pears and Cool Whip.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish. Set in refrigerator until firm.

title: picnic macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cool water.
Combine cooked macaroni with remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Chill.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine milk and cherry juice.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to shortening mixture, flour and milk mixtures, alternately beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add cherries before last flour addition.
Mix nuts with last flour and add to batter.
Beat mixture well!
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour the boiled vinegar mixture over vegetables and refrigerate several hours before serving.
This will keep well in the refrigerator.

title: pear-custard pie
directions: Peel, halve and core pears; brush with lemon juice.
Place pears, cut side down, in pastry shell, with narrow end toward center.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in flour, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour over pears.
Sprinkle lightly with mace.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until filling is set and top is lightly browned.
Cool on cake rack for 1 hour or longer, before cutting. Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Best if served same day.

title: german cabbage salad
directions: Fry bacon and retain 1/2 the grease in pan.
Cut cabbage into thin strips.
Stir-fry in bacon grease no longer than 3 minutes. Mix with vinegar and crumbled bacon.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: shrimp crabmeat casserole
directions: Cook rice; mix shrimp and crabmeat with rice.
Then add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crumble angel food cake and pound cake in a large mixing bowl. Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cap strawberries and mix in glaze.
Pour over mixture in cake pan. Refrigerate before serving.

title: refrigerator cookies(pinwheels)
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together.
Place in dish or pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini squash pie
directions: Mix Bisquick, eggs, basil, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add cheese, squash and onion.
Pour into pie plate sprayed with Pam. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°, or until center of pie is dry when pricked with a toothpick.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use for chicken, steaks or wings!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper.
Mix equal portions of mayonnaise and sour cream, about 1/2 cup each.
Spread over top of salad.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage until it changes color and layer them in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: challah bread
directions: Add all ingredients in order listed.
Set bread maker at white bread setting.

title: deer stew
directions: Boil deer stew for 4 to 5 hours.
Clean potatoes, carrots and onions.
Add vegetables to deer roast and cook for 6 hours.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Beat egg yolk until light; gradually stir in beer and Tabasco. Sift in flour, salt, pepper and paprika; mix well.
Stir in butter. Beat egg white until stiff but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Dip onion rings, a few at a time, into batter.
Heat deep fat with basket in place to 370°.
Add onion rings a few at a time.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
If desired, fry ahead and reheat in 400° oven.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Grease 10 to 12 muffin cups.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In second bowl, beat oil, egg, milk and almond extract until smooth.
Add to dry ingredients and mix until only moistened.
Stir in poppy seed.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, until golden brown.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together and heat tuna, soup and eggs.
Put chow mein noodles on bottom.
Put mixture on top in 2-quart dish.

title: chilled green bean salad
directions: Wash, trim and cut green beans into bite-sized pieces.
Fill a large pan with 1 inch of water.
Bring to a boil and add green beans.
Cook for 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Combine the green beans with all other ingredients.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal raisin bread
directions: Combine oatmeal, sugar, salt, shortening, molasses and boiling water together.
Cool to lukewarm, then add yeast, warm water, raisins and flour.
Knead and let rise.
Put in pans.
Let raise and bake at 350°.

title: crab spread
directions: Place the cream cheese block on a plate.
Pick over the crab meat to remove cartilage.
Place
the
crab on top of the cream cheese.
Pour the
chili sauce over the cream cheese and crab. Serve with crackers.
Quick and easy.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, combine all ingredients.
Toss until coated.
Empty into shallow baking dish. Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with chopped fresh parsley, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: gram's lighter applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Beat in 2 eggs, one at a time, along with the vanilla.
Add the remaining ingredients and blend until all is incorporated.
Divide the batter among 3 greased loaf pans, approximately 8 x 4 x 3 inches each.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove to a cooling rack.
When cool enough to handle, remove the loaves from the pans and cool completely on the rack.
Wrap in plastic wrap and keep in refrigerator.

title: granola cookies
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar.
Blend in egg, milk and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: fudge pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, at 375°.

title: knock-u-sox-off cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
While hot, punch holes in cake and pour caramel topping on the cake.
Pour milk over top of cake.
Sprinkle one half of the Heath Bits on top. Let cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip and then sprinkle with remaining Heath Bits.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cook in apple cider until apples are soft, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Prepare filling in saucepan.
Combine rhubarb, berries and lemon juice.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes. Combine sugar and cornstarch, stir into saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set aside.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow, and sympathy. Fold in four cups of prayers and faith to lighten all other ingredients and raise texture to great heights of character. After flouring this into your daily life, bake well, with heat of human kindness.

title: caraway cabbage(microwave)
directions: In oblong baking dish, heat butter on High in microwave 1 minute or until melted.
Cut cabbage up and place in baking dish. Brush the cabbage with butter.
Sprinkle with caraway.
Cover and cook on High for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes, covered, before eating.

title: dark brown bread
directions: Mix together the cornmeal, flour, milk powder, soda and salt. Add the molasses and mix thoroughly.
Add the racing, boiling water.
Mix quickly so that all the meal and flour will be well scalded.

The results will be a soup dough, like cake batter. Grease with oleo 2 one pound coffee cans and fill with batter so that there are at least 1 1/2 inches of air space at the top. Cover with aluminum foil (bright side down) and tie foil on around tops of cans.
Place on a rack one inch off the bottom in a large kettle of boiling water which comes 2/3 of the way up the cans. Cover kettle and steam for 5 1/2 to 6 hours.
Watch the water level while steaming to maintain the 2/3 coverage.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, add cocoa, cornstarch and sugar.
Add enough milk (about 1/4 cup) to make a paste.
Stir until smooth. Slowly add 3 cups of milk; stir after each cup.
Cook over medium heat and stir constantly, until it comes to a boil.
Take off heat and add vanilla and butter.
Put whipping cream on top!

title: tex mex dip
directions: Layer each ingredient in order in a casserole dish.
Place in refrigerator to set for at least two hours.
Serve with chips.

title: honey salad dressing(good on fruit salad)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well with beater until well blended.
Better if made in advance.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients, then pour in mixture of remaining ingredients.
Toss until well blended.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder 3 times.
Add flour and milk to creamed mixture.
Add extracts.
Divide evenly in 3 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks.
Make sure cake bottom is next to rack.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine first four ingredients and cook in heavy saucepan on low heat about 30 minutes, until forms soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat and add butter and powdered sugar.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls on foil or waxed paper.
Cool.

title: the "one" cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugars together in large bowl.
Add vanilla, oil and egg.
Sift together baking soda, cream of tartar and flour and add; then add oats, coconut and Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: seafood enchilada
directions: Mix yogurt, sour cream, onion and chili salsa. Pour enchilada sauce in bowl. Fry tortillas in hot oil until soft. Drain. Add sauce to coat. Place in 9 x 13 pan. Add part cream and cheese; repeat. Pour sauce and seafood. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend with electric mixer.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with assorted fruits.
Makes 4 cups.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Layer in order as listed, except for mayonnaise, sugar, bacon and cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar; cover layers with this, being sure to seal edges.
Put grated cheese on top of this with crisp bacon bits (about 8 slices, cooked).
Cover dish and refrigerate about 12 hours.

title: sweet and sour vegetables
directions: Combine broccoli, carrots and bell pepper in a large nonstick skillet with tight fitting lid.
Add water; bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and steam 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: sourdough bread rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.

title: best ever molded aspic salad
directions: You
can use 1 cup chili sauce or 1/2 cup
catsup,
1/2 cocktail sauce, etc. or 1 can of Veg-All.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Wash and salt chicken.
Combine soups, water and rice in flat casserole.
Lay salted chicken pieces on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add Mazola and mix.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Roll in small balls and roll in white sugar.
Press with glass or fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: tex mex spice dip
directions: Make a batch of this spice mix to use in Sante Fe Skinny Dip, tortillas, soup and Chicken Taco Salad.
Save leftovers.
Mix to use in any recipe that needs a little zip.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with your favorite fruit.

title: banana split smoothie
directions: In blender, place ice cream, bananas, syrup, sugar and vanilla. Cover; blend on high speed until smooth.
Add ice; blend until well mixed.
Garnish with whipped cream, banana slice and cherries if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: delicious
directions: In 1 1/2-quart baking dish (Corning Ware), melt butter.
Mix milk, sugar and flour together.
Pour on top of butter.
Do not stir.
Drain fruit good, then pour fruit in center.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown and center is done.
Center will be a little moist if fruit has not been drained good, but that is okay. This is delicious!

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and salt alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Dissolve soda in hot water; mix with vinegar, holding over bowl, as it will foam! Quickly add mixture to batter.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Toss the thinly sliced cucumbers with the salt in a small bowl.
Chill for 30 minutes or until most of the liquid has drained off.
Squeeze the remaining liquid from the cucumber slices and pat dry on paper towel.
Place in salad bowl and fold in onion, garlic, vinegar, sugar and cold water. You may garnish with tomatoes and green peppers.
May be served plain or with sour cream.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip; mix well.
Cut bananas into pudding.
Line dish with wafers and alternate until all pudding is used.
Crumble a wafer or two and sprinkle over top.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut-butter chews
directions: Bring to boil the sugar and white syrup.
Remove from heat, then add peanut butter and butter.
Stir well, then add corn flakes.
Stir until completely coated.
Butter fingers to make a ball shape while mixture is still hot.
Place on wax paper until cooled.

title: orange gelatin
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add buttermilk.
Stir until cool.
Fold in whipped cream and pecans.
Spoon into a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel avocados and mash with tomatoes; mix remaining ingredients and chill 1 hour.

title: avocado and egg salad
directions: Combine eggs, onions and tomatoes. Scoop out avocado shells, leaving shells firm; brush with a little lemon juice. Cube avocado pulp and stir in remaining ingredients. add egg mixture and spoon into avocado shells. Sprinkle bacon on top.

title: super-duper chocolate cookies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate; add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs singly, beating after each.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture with nuts; mix well.
Chill dough several hours.
Form into small balls; roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: mexican wedding bells
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour, pecans and vanilla.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased sheet pan and flatten slightly.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Roll in additional confectioners sugar while hot.
When cool, roll in sugar again.
Yields 25 to 30 balls.

title: angel hair pasta with clam sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet, add butter and melt.
Add garlic, stirring to saute and then add juice from clams and bring mixture to boil.
Add anchovies and simmer.
Reduce liquid to about half, about 10 minutes.
Add minced clams and heat thoroughly.
Pour over cooked pasta, toss and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix (by hand) dry pudding mix and pineapple (juice also). Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans. Mix well. That's it!

title: doughnuts
directions: For chocolate, omit nutmeg and add 5 tablespoons cocoa.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine.
Take away from heat.
Add cocoa and peanut butter.
Gradually add confectioners sugar.
Press into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour and serve.

title: drop molasses cookies
directions: Add flour to stiffen for a drop cookie.
Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: taco salad
directions: Saute the beef with the seasonings until done.
Drain very well.
Keep at room temperature. Combine and toss all the ingredients with the dressing.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream the sugars, oleo, eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add dry ingredients, adding to creamed mixture.
Add the remainder of ingredients.
Drop by large tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned. Makes a huge amount, but recipe is easily cut in half.

title: english trifle
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Let cool and crumble into a large bowl.
Slice strawberries and lay half on top of cake.
Layer sliced peaches on strawberries.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip and put on top of peaches.
Place strawberries on Cool Whip.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir Jell-O in cottage cheese; add fruit cocktail, then Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Stir all together; chill and serve.

title: corn beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients (EXCEPT bread and dressing) in a slow cooker; mix well.
Cover and cook on high 1-2 hours or until heated well, stirring occasionally.
Turn to low and keep warm in cooker. Put spread on rye bread slices.
Top with dressing if desired.

title: scotland school casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, peel and slice potatoes.
Place alternating layers of potatoes, cut up hot dogs, slices of cheese, diced onion and mushrooms and add the milk.
Bake in a 350° oven until potatoes are soft.
Cover with aluminum foil for first 1/2 hour.

title: candy bar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 25 degrees. Cream butter until light and fluffy; gradually add sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Add remaining ingredients and pour into prepared bundt pan. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done. Yields 12 slices.

title: beat 'n eat frosting
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a small deep bowl.
Add boiling water.
Beat to stiff peaks.

title: orange cream special
directions: Cook to 230°.
Boil without stirring (except occasionally). Cool.
Beat until stiff, add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook the squash, cut in slices, in 1-inch of water until tender with 1 teaspoon salt. Drain and mash.
Mix together eggs (beaten well), butter, cheese, onion and sugar.
Pour in casserole. Cover with crumbs. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gold cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add one egg at a time to mixture. Then add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: In large bowl, make several layers of carrots, pepper and onions, alternating each vegetable and salting and peppering each layer.
Mix together soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix butter and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Crush 1/2 cup blueberries with fork.
Mix in.
Fold in 2 cups blueberries.
Sprinkle with 3 teaspoons sugar. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: (You may want to add more mayonnaise or tomato according to your taste.)

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut meat into small strips.
Marinate overnight in the seasoning mixture, stirring several times.
Drain; pat with paper towel.
Place meat on shallow pan or on rack or hang by toothpicks.
Place in oven at 140° for several hours until meat is dry.

title: pickled pig feet
directions: Place clean pig's feet in a pot and cover with cold water. Bring to a rapid boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 4 to 6 hours or until tender.
Near the end of cooking time, add salt to taste to the water.
Drain pig's feet, put in a gallon jug and cover with heated vinegar.
Cover and store for 2 days or longer in refrigerator.
You can seal them in the jar and they will keep for several weeks.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: pickled mushrooms in brine
directions: Clean the mushrooms and slice in quarters or thirds, according to size. Combine 1 tablespoon salt, vinegar, water, rosemary, a few peppercorns, bay leaves, onion and garlic in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Cook 15 minutes.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix all of the last 6 ingredients together well.
Fold into the macaroni and cheese mixture.
Drizzle about 3 tablespoons margarine or butter over casserole.
Sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix (cornbread or herb) or can use crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until casserole is bubbly all the way through.

title: white bread for automatic bread machine
directions: Add all ingredients in the order listed into a large automatic bread machine and push start.
We go through a loaf of bread a day and this recipe consistently rises and bakes nicely.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Chop green tomatoes in blender; beat eggs together with oil and sugar.
Add green tomatoes; add vanilla.
Beat.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add fruit and oats to sugar mixture.
Gradually add flour mixture and raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 4 loaf pans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake for approximately 1 hour in 350° oven.
Makes a super moist bread.
I like it better than zucchini bread.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange cooked chicken and broccoli in square baking dish. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: walnut chicken salad
directions: Toss nuts in soy sauce.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes or until brown and toasted.
Cover pan with foil to avoid burning. Mix lettuce, grapes, walnuts and chicken in bowl.
Cover with dressing and serve.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add milk gradually; stir until mixed.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil one minute. Remove from heat; blend in egg yolks.
Stir in butter and vanilla, then cool.
Pour into cooked pie crust.

title: english muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water to right consistency.
Knead for a few minutes until smooth.
Grease enough cookie sheets to hold 2 dozen muffins.
Pull off a ball of dough about 3-inches in diameter.
Roll around.
Place on sheet.
Flatten until 1/4-inch thick.
Cover; allow to rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Bake first 7 minutes and turn over for rest of time. Yields 2 dozen.

title: granny's jam cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 300° until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and syrup. Place 1 cup broken pecan pieces in uncooked pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: southwestern muffins
directions: Saute peppers and onion in 2 tablespoons oil until tender; stir in ham.
Combine cornmeal and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients; add to dry ingredients with pepper mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yield: about 2 dozen.

title: meringue for pie
directions: In mixer bowl, beat egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar at medium speed of electric mixer for about 1 minute or until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, about 1 tablespoon at a time, beating at high speed for about 4 minutes or until mixture forms stiff, glossy peaks.
Spread over pie, carefully sealing to edge to prevent shrinkage.
Bake at 350° just until meringue turns golden, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Break up bread.
Dice onion; add salt, pepper and sage.
Add enough water to make moist.
Beat eggs.
Add to mix.
Add enough broth to be moist.

title: maple meltaways
directions: Put margarine, sugar, salt and maple flavoring in large bowl. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and blend in.

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Add chocolate bits to taste.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon onto baking sheet.
Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix altogether.
Put in oblong pan that has been greased well.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: russian chicken breasts
directions: Mix sour cream and salad dressing.
Season chicken breast halves.
Spray shallow glass baking dish with Pam.
Place chicken in baking dish and pour sauce over it.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Uncover and cook about 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Mix all together.
Grease crock-pot.
Cook on low for 3 1/2 hours.

title: company dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk and cool.
Whip cream and add pineapple, nuts and cherries to marshmallow mixture.
Line pan (9 x 12 x 2-inch) with crushed graham crackers and pour mixture over crackers.
Cool in refrigerator until served.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Goes well with fruit and vegetables.
Good idea for children's lunch boxes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef; mix in flour and add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook in frying pan and let stand on simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serve with cooked egg noodles.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile, brown sausage in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Combine sausage and remaining ingredients in Pam sprayed 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels and melted butter.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish for 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over pretzels.
Mix Jell-O and water.
Add thawed strawberries.
Pour over Cool Whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix this all together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: miniature quiche
directions: Mix all as pastry; roll into small
balls.
Press
into small muffin pans with finger.

title: chicken made easy
directions: Mix water, sour cream and cream of chicken soup together.
Put chicken breasts in crock-pot.
Pour broth over breasts and let simmer 6 to 8 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut up all vegetables.
Add California blend, thawed.
Mix in Ranch dressing.
Let sit for 4 hours or overnight.

title: cabbage and white bean soup
directions: Heat oil and butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion; saute 3 minutes.
Add carrots and celery; saute 3 minutes. Add caraway seed; cook, stirring, 1 minute.
Stir in cabbage, water and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: spinach maria
directions: Cook spinach according to package. Drain. Saut onion in butter and add cream cheese and Parmesan cheese. Cook until cream cheese is melted. Add cayenne pepper. Mix in spinach. Put in baking dish. Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: company beef patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 5 patties. Encircle each patty with bacon strip and secure with toothpick (filet mignon appearance).	Place patties on broiler rack and broil 7 inches from source of heat for 6 minutes.
Turn over and broil 6 more minutes.
I sometimes wrap the bacon around the patty and grill in my George Foreman grill.

title: creamy garlic spinach soup
directions: Remove stalks from the spinach and coarsely chop.
Grate the carrots.
Combine spinach with chicken broth and carrots in a 2 to 3-quart pot.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes until carrots are tender and spinach wilted.
Remove from heat.

title: icing for any cake
directions: In a bowl, mix together ingredients.
Stir to mix well. Mixture should be smooth and creamy and ready to use.

title: velveeta cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into small pieces; place in crock-pot on high setting.
Lightly brown beef and sausage; drain off all grease. Pour over cheese that is thoroughly melted.
Mix the soups (undiluted) with the tomatoes; heat until soups are runny.
Pour into crock-pot with other ingredients.
Heat until well blended. Delicious served with chips.

title: mary tucker's best persimmon pudding
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a mixer.
Add milk, flour, persimmon pulp and baking soda alternately.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.
Refrigerate after cooking.
Serve cold with sweetened whipped cream on top.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in a large bowl; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Cook and stir just until the sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumber mixture; cool.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.
Yield: 6 cups.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: red oak fire department chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off excess grease.
Put other ingredients in pot and let simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: barbecue venison
directions: Put all ingredients in a 4-quart pressure cooker.
Cook on 10 pounds pressure for 45 minutes.
Drain meat and place in baking dish.
Separate meat with fork.
Mix approximately 18 ounces of your favorite barbecue sauce.
Add enough sauce to the meat mixture until it is slightly soupy.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve on sandwiches or as a casserole.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add eggs to creamed mixture, one at a time. Blend well. Add crushed bananas and nuts. Sift flour and soda together; add to mixture. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Bake in a well greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: elfrieda's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain, rinse and cool.
Cut up green pepper, onion and carrots.
Mix with macaroni.
Mix sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and Eagle Brand milk together.
Add to macaroni.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in half at joint.
Spread in broiler pan and broil about 25 minutes or until browned, turning occasionally.
In a small saucepan, heat Tabasco, butter and vinegar.
Drizzle evenly over wings.
Serve with celery sticks and salad dressing for dipping.
Great for appetizers or "Pig Out" for a meal.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 2 1/2-quart dish for 1 1/4 hours at 375°.
Baking time will depend on the size of the container.
Makes 12 generous servings.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix together with mixer until well blended.
Put into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 1 hour. When firm, but not hard, it is done.

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Place fruit in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut crust from bread and cut each slice into 4 fingers.
Place bread fingers over fruit.
In bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and butter.
Pour over fruit and bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until light brown on top.
Can sprinkle nutmeg on top of bread, if desired.

title: maple oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together the oats, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the cream, syrup, oleo, nuts and egg (optional).
Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mash cheese in a bowl.
Add flavoring and coloring.
Mix in sugar.
Combine and knead with hands until like pie dough.
Roll in balls the size of marbles.
Place one side in small amount of granulated sugar.
Press sugar side in mold.
Unmold at once. (Soft flexible rubber molds are best for this recipe.)

title: spinach spread(makes about 4 cups)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and blend thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Crumble and fry sausage for a few minutes.
Drain grease.
Add Bisquick.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add to sausage and Bisquick.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 100 to 150 balls.

title: margie's blueberry icebox pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice with mixer.
Fold in blueberries and pecans.
Fill pie crusts and chill.
(Fresh or frozen blueberries may be used.)

title: farmhouse rolls
directions: In a very large bowl, dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar and let stand for five minutes.
Stir in egg, butter (or oil), and salt.
Stir in as much flour as you can.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead in as much flour as you can to make a moderately stiff dough shaped into a ball.
Put into greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Divide in half. Let rest ten minutes.
Grease baking pans.
Divide into individual rolls.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Brush with melted butter. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown steak on both sides.
Combine vegetables and water and pour over steak.
Simmer at 200° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sheri's faux caviar and new potatoes
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until fork-tender. Drain and cut each in half. Scoop a dollop of sour cream on each potato half. Top with ripe olives.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bubbly and brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheesie potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Add all ingredients, except corn flakes and melted margarine, and stir to mix.
For topping, mix crushed corn flakes and 1/8 c. melted margarine.
Cover potatoes with topping and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
