Can be prepared a day ahead.

title: johnny bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
In a small
bowl,
mix
eggs, then combine eggs with dry mixture. Blend at
low
speed
until
well
mixed.
Add oil, pecans and strawberries.
Pour batter into well-greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken mushroom casserole
directions: Dip chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Dip pieces in melted butter (about 1/2 stick).
Put in pan to brown at 400°.
When brown (about 1/2 hour), mix soup, mushrooms, wine and water.
Pour around chicken (not over it). Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, tightly covered with foil.
The gravy is delicious served over rice.
Serves 4.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in regular oven (350°) for about 15 to 20 minutes, until top is browned and bubbly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in broth and drain.
Put butter, onion and green pepper in skillet and saute.
Add all the ingredients to drained spaghetti.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Blend egg yolks and vanilla, then mix with sugar and butter.
Add flour and salt to mixture.
Chill in refrigerator 1 hour before pressing.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: white wine pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into a tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.
Let cake cool in pan for 35 minutes before putting on cake plate then glaze.

title: apple cider beef stew
directions: Mix together flour, salt and pepper and coat beef

chunks. Brown meat in heated oil. In large pot put meat with apple juice, lemon juice and seasonings. Bring to a boil. Simmer covered about 1-1/2 hours. Add vegetables and apple cider. Cook 20 more minutes or until vegetables are tender. Garnish with parsley.

title: chinese spinach
directions: Cut fresh spinach stems into 3-inch pieces.
Tear leaves into bite size pieces.
Cook, covered, in a very small amount of water. Reduce heat when steam forms.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, turning frequently with a fork.
Drain well.
Heat oil, sugar and soy sauce in a skillet. Add spinach, water chestnuts and onion.
Cook, tossing lightly, 2 to 3 minutes or until spinach is coated and heated.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and coating of flour and fry quickly on both sides in margarine.
Remove chicken from fry pan and saute onions, pepper and tomato, only until wilted (not brown).
Add more margarine, if needed.
Add paprika and chicken broth.
Bring to a quick boil, adding chicken pieces.
Baste with liquid, cover and simmer until tender.
Remove chicken to casserole to keep hot.
Add sour cream to liquid in fry pan and heat, do not boil.
Pour over chicken.
Serve with rice, noodles or egg dumplings.

title: fillets of round
directions: Combine milk, eggs, crumbs, onions, salt and pepper; blend well.
Add ground round and mix lightly; allow to stand 5 minutes in the oven.
Shape into thick patties, 4 to 6; circle each patty with a bacon strip and secure with a toothpick.
Place in a preheated broiler; broil on each side until browned, about 6 minutes. Can be cooked on grill.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Layer 1/2 cake and sprinkle 1 teaspoon sherry.
Layer 1/2 pudding, 1/2 fruit filling and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers and let set overnight.
This dessert looks pretty in a glass bowl.

title: chicken and broccoli soup
directions: Put potatoes and onion	in
just
enough
water to cook them. Do not drain.
Cook broccoli
for 10 minutes and add to potatoes. Add other ingredients and enough water if needed to get the consistency you want.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring until well blended.
Add marshmallow cream and vanilla and beat until well blended.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature and refrigerate.
Cut into squares when firm. Makes 3 pounds of candy.

title: irish stew
directions: Trim excess fat from meat; cut meat into small pieces.
Peel and slice onions and potatoes, making thick slices.
Layer sliced potatoes on bottom of casserole.
Add layer of lamb and layer of onions.
Sprinkle seasonings and herbs over the top; top off with potato slices.
Add water.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Add sugars and margarine.
Beat well and add eggs.
Beat well.
Add about 1/2 of chocolate bits.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate bits and walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: thanksgiving pudding
directions: Heat grape juice to boiling point; add gelatin and stir.
Add egg yolks which have been creamed with sugar.
Have egg whites beaten stiff; add to grape juice mixture and blend thoroughly. Remove from stove.
In large bowl, alternate layers of wafers, cherries and nuts until all are used.
Pour grape juice mixture over this and place in refrigerator to set.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes a large amount.

title: yumbug nut ring
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter, sour cream, vanilla and almond filling.
Blend well, beating three minutes at medium speed.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix at low speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 to 10-inch Bundt pan and bake for 60 to 65 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 hour, do not invert! Remove from pan.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Clean and chop broccoli.
Add raisins and onions.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add dressing and bacon when ready to serve.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix the sugar, milk and margarine together; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove.
Stir in peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish and let cool before slicing.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Note:
All ingredients should be room temperature.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Put sugar, water, raisins, shortening, cinnamon and cloves in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Sift flour and blend in soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to raisin mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry refrigerator cake
directions: Mix together cranberries, banana and sugar.
Set aside.
Place half of crushed vanilla wafers in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan. Cream margarine and powdered sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Spread this mixture over th crushed wafers and top with a layer of cranberry-banana mixture.
Spread whipped cream over top and sprinkle nuts over whipped cream.
Add remaining crushed wafers over top and chill for at least 4 hours or overnight. Serves 9.

title: broiled ham and pineapple slices
directions: Set oven at 550°.
Remove outer fat on ham.
Place ham on a rack in a broiler pan.
Broil 3 inches from the heat for 5 minutes on each side until light brown.
During the last 2 minutes of broiling, arrange pineapple slices on ham.
Brush slices with butter.

title: cornish game hens and rice
directions: Spread rice in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown, stir while browning.
Combine dressing with 2 1/2 cups boiling water, add soup and stir.
Add to rice.
Cut hens in half, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar and milk in sauce pan and bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add marshmallows and peanut butter and stir until marshmallows and peanut butter are dissolved. Pour into 8 x 8 inch pan and chill. Add nuts if desired.

title: florentine stuffed shells
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan stir cornstarch, milk, salt and hot sauce until smooth (stir constantly so it won't scorch).
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add Parmesan and ketchup, stirring until smooth.
Remove 1/4 cup sauce; reserve.
In large skillet, at medium-high heat, saute turkey and garlic for about 3 minutes.
Stir in spinach, cottage cheese and 1/4 cup reserved sauce.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons mixture into each shell.
Place shells in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish; top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
This recipe can be made ahead and kept in the refrigerator.
Just heat in oven a little longer. Makes 4 servings.

title: bugle surprises
directions: Spoon peanut butter into a small plastic bag.
Snip a hole in corner of bag.
Squeeze a small amount of peanut butter into each corn snack.
Drop each into chocolate coating and place on wax paper to dry.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: oriental london broil marinade
directions: Score steak and place in shallow dish.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour half over steak.
Marinate 6 hours; turn steak occasionally.
Refrigerate unused half of marinade.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix well and shape in narrow loaf.
Put in refrigerator overnight or 8 hours.
Slice in pieces.
Roll in flour, then fry until brown.
Put in roaster.
Pour mushroom soup diluted with 1 can water over meat.
Bake in slow oven for 2 hours (300° to 325°).

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook rice in 1 1/4 cups milk.
Remove cabbage leaves from head and immerse in boiling, salted water.
Cook until partially translucent and pliable; drain.
Combine meats with 1 cup milk, salt, pepper and rice; mix thoroughly.
Spoon meat mixture on each leaf.
Roll and tie securely or fasten with toothpicks.
Brown rolls in hot fat; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Add water.
Cover and cook slowly about 2 hours.
Thicken broth for gravy.

title: butterscotch apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Arrange apples in 9 x 13 baking pan.
Combine morsels, sugar, flour and cinnamon in small bowl, sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 20 minutes, remove from oven.

title: hamantashen
directions: Sift flour; cream butter and cheese together until well-blended.
Gradually add flour; make a ball of dough and put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out (not too thin) on floured surface.
Cut into circles.
Put 1/2 teaspoon filling in the center and fold to form triangles.
Bake on a greased pan at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into mixing bowl. Blend in vegetable oil with fork or pastry blender.
Add milk. Mix until dough forms. Gently knead on lightly floured board 15 to 20 times.
Roll out or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 450° oven until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 12 biscuits.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish, add onion soup and stir until dissolved.
Add rice, stir and add consomme soup and can of water. Add sliced mushrooms, stir well again.
Put foil over Pyrex dish and put lid on top also.
Stir when half way baked.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pecan clusters(1989 champion winner pecan fest)
directions: Combine pecans and melted butter on large cookie sheet.
Toast in oven (350°) until lightly browned.
Stir frequently.
Salt and place on paper towels and blot pecans to remove excess fat.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple, 1/2 cup nuts, green pepper, onions and salt.
Shape into ball. Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in clear plastic or foil and refrigerate overnight or unti well chilled.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan twists(using rich sweet dough)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat, but not boil.
Pour in pans. Sprinkle with pecans or walnuts.

title: green stuff
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together until well blended.
Add Cool Whip.
Blend and refrigerate.
Good as salad or dessert.

title: swiss steak
directions: Oil pan enough to brown meat. Dip meat in flour, salt and pepper and lay in the oil until thoroughly browned. Pour in the tomatoes; boil slowly. Pour in the carrots (try to place them low down in the pan). Pour in onions and cover after boil. Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours on simmer. Serves 4 to 6.

title: basil-garlic pesto
directions: In a small skillet, bring the broth and garlic to a boil; reduce the heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 4 minutes or until the garlic is tender.
Transfer the broth and garlic to a food processor or blender; add the basil, walnuts, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper and whirl for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Add the oil and blend for 10 seconds.
Serve immediately over pasta.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: best cheesecake
directions: Blend cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup butter and 1/4 cup sugar and press into and up sides of spring-form pan. Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add remaining 1 cup sugar and vanilla extract. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Blend in sour cream. Spread in prepared pan. (If desired, you can add four one ounce blocks of melted chocolate before spreading into pan.) Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until firm. Turn off oven; leave oven door slightly ajar and allow cheesecake to remain in oven for 1 hour. Chill overnight.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots diagonally in 1/4-inch slices, cook and drain. Mix sugar and flour in medium sized saucepan.
Stir in orange juice.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low, stir in butter.
Simmer 2 minutes until thickened.
Add carrots, stir to coat and glaze.
Makes 10 servings.

title: shortcut pan rolls
directions: Combine grits, sugar and salt in large bowl of mixer.
Add water, oil and 2 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes on low.
Add 1 cup additional flour and yeast.
Beat 1 minute on low.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on well floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into 18 balls.
Place in 2 greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Cover.
Let rise 1 hour or until nearly double in size.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and brush with margarine.
Serve warm.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix can of drained tuna and cream cheese, garlic, chopped onion, mustard, salad dressing and chopped pimento.
Use as a dip or place on small cracker.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix, cover and chill until hard.
Roll about 1/3 of the dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on a flour cloth covered board.
Keep remaining dough chilled.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Transfer onto wax paper, heavily covered with granulated sugar, so each side is well covered.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick each round with a fork 4 times.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until nice and brown.
Put cookies together in pairs with creamy filling.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Press zucchini between paper towels to remove excess moisture. Combine zucchini, eggs, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and flour in a medium bowl; stir well.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven; brush surface with oil.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread spaghetti sauce on top of zucchini mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, oregano and red pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° an additional 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peas with onions and bacon
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, brown bacon for about 3 minutes.
Add onions and saute another 3 minutes or until onions are tender.
Add peas, salt, pepper and reduce heat, cook for 5 minutes. Serve.

title: sour cream pralines
directions: Combine sugars, baking soda, salt, sour cream and corn syrup in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat to thread stage (230° on candy thermometer), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat in butter, vanilla and pecans.
Cool to warm, then beat until mixture begins to lose its sheen.
Working rapidly to prevent candy from setting, drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. If candy begins to set, return to heat or put pot in a bowl of boiling water until mixture is soft and smooth.
When set and cool, remove pralines to a tray.
Makes about 36.

title: holiday sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Add other ingredients in same order listed. Alternate flour and sour cream.
Bake in greased and floured pan (tube) 1 hour at 350°.
Leave cake in pan ov covered.

title: mother's pink salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Drain pineapple juice and add to lemon juice to make 1/2 cup.
Mix Jell-O, juices and Miracle Whip; let partially jell.
Fold other ingredients into Jell-O mixture and jell.

title: pecan praline cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold in brown sugar, pecans and salt, mixing thoroughly.
Add flour and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets, about 2-inches apart. Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely before removing from cookie sheets.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in boiling salt water.
Cool and remove chicken from bones.
Cut in small pieces and combine with first five ingredients.
Put in casserole and top with saltines which have been coated with cooking oil.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add to wet ingredients.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: boula boula soup(potage de tortue)
directions: Gently blend above ingredients.
Simmer on low heat until thoroughly warmed.
Garnish with thin ring of red onions.

title: potato-stuffed franks
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on package.
Mix potatoes, onion, parsley and mustard.
Split frankfurters lengthwise, not cutting completely through.
Spread frankfurters open; place cut sides up on rack in broiler pan.
Spread with potato mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Set oven control to broil and/or 500°.
Broil frankfurters with tops about 5 inches from heat until cheese is melted, 5 to 8 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Measure juice from cherries and pineapple; add enough water to make 2 cups.
Pour into saucepan and heat to a boil.
Add jello and dissolve.
Let jello set and chill.
Add remaining ingredients and allow to congeal.
Refrigerate.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Fry hamburger; add onion and drain. Mix together in large roaster pan spaghetti, soups, hamburger and tomato juice.
Mix well. Cut slivers of butter and put on top. Cover with lid or foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aimee's aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 can of V-8 juice; set aside.
Bring to a boil first 7 ingredients and lower heat and cook for about 5 minutes.
Fold gelatin mixture into hot mixture.
Pour into bowl and chill until mixture begins to congeal.
Stir in clams, celery, etc.
Pour into a large salad mold or individual molds.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: glazed ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients (except marmalade) together very well! Press into buttered loaf pan and bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven. Remove from oven and spread with marmalade.
Return to oven for another 1/2 hour.
Will serve 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.

title: fried cheese
directions: Dip cheese cubes into egg whites, then in crumbs; let dry a few minutes, then repeat coating.
Pour corn oil into heavy 3-quart saucepan filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat to 375°.
Fry cheese a few pieces at a time, 1 minute or until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes about 24 1-inch cubes.

title: babootie
directions: Cut crust from a slice of buttered bread.
Fit slice into a greased muffin cup.
Drop egg into the slice and season.
Bake until white is firm and bread is toasted.
(Also, can slightly scramble egg before putting in the bread cup.)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine potatoes, butter, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: veggie pizza
directions: *Use any of all of the following:
red pepper, green pepper, onion (red), cauliflower, broccoli, celery.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cut lengthwise in thick slices. Arrange in baking dish.
Mix sugar and water and bring to a boil. Pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Add chopped nut meats.
Beat egg; mix with milk.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing lightly.
Pour into greased pan lined with waxed paper.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: brie puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On a lightly floured surface, use a 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter to cut out rounds from each pastry piece. Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Transfer to wire rack; cool completely. Carefully slice tops off puffs.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon preserves onto bottom halves of puffs.
In large bowl, mix cheese and sherry until well blended.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon cheese mixture over preserves.
Replace tops.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: chocolate peanut dessert
directions: Cut butter into flour until crumbly.
Add 3/4 cup of the chopped peanuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chili for 100
directions: Cook until beans are tender.
Serve with shredded cheese, salsa, crackers and chopped onions.
Approximate cost: $95.00.

title: janet's banana punch
directions: Mix bananas in blender or processor until "mushy".
Boil water and sugar, then cool.
Mix all ingredients and freeze.
When ready for use, defrost in punch bowl adding ginger ale and/or Sprite.
I always add almond flavoring to taste.

title: glazed corned beef
directions: Place corned beef in large kettle; cover with water and simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Combine jelly, lemon and orange peel and juice in small saucepan; heat until jelly melts.
Remove corned beef from water to shallow baking pan.
Arrange apricots and pineapple around meat.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Glaze often as you bake.
Serves 8.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown ground beef and add remaining ingredients.
Spread in uncooked pastry shell.
Spread cheese topping over meat filling.
Bake about 30 minutes, until cheese is browned on top and serve in wedges with sauce.

title: angel biscuits #1
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add with buttermilk to dry mixture; mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured board and roll to desired thickness.
Cut into biscuits and bake for 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and add sauce, spices and 1 cup cheese. Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with tortillas.
Pour in meat mixture.
Add another layer of tortillas.
Pour soup and milk mix over the top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brandied fruit starter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a nonmetal bowl.
Stir gently and let stand at room temperature for 3 weeks.
Stir twice a week. Serve over ice cream or pound cake.
Always reserve at least 1 cup starter.
To replenish starter, add 1 cup sugar and one of the first 4 ingredients every 1 to 3 weeks, alternating fruits each time.
Stir gently; cover and let stand at room temperature 3 days before using.
Yields 6 cups.

title: fat soft pretzels
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Add the sugar and salt.
Add the flour a cup at a time, stirring as you go.
When the dough no longer sticks to the sides of the bowl, place the dough on a floured surface and knead about 5 minutes. Divide the dough into 16 balls.
Roll the balls into ropes about 12 inches long.
Shape the ropes into pretzels.
Place the pretzels on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Brush the pretzels with egg white and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients, shape into loaf, bake at 350° about 1 hour. Baste with drippings occasionally.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush
Oreo
cookies
in blender or food processor.
Mix with melted butter and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Spread
softened vanilla ice cream on the Oreo crust and return
to freezer.
Mix sugar, cream and chocolate; bring to boil and
cook
until thick.
Stir as it cooks.
When cool, spread over ice cream.
Return to freezer.
To serve, top with Cool Whip, cherries and pecans.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Mix flour with cheese.
Add black pepper, cumin seed, salt and butter.
Blend well and make a stiff dough.
Divide dough into 3 portions.
Knead and make patties.
Using a little flour on a surface, roll each patty large and round.
Cut into small squares and drop into heated oil.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Finish the rest of the dough in the same manner.

title: scotch bread
directions: Beat together, roll out fairly thin and cut in small diamonds, strips, etc., as this will get larger when baked.
Bake in hot oven at 425°.

title: five pound fudge
directions: Combine in heavy 4-quart saucepan butter, sugar and evaporated milk.
Boil 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, chocolate and vanilla.
Beat well until mixed.
Add walnuts, coarsely chopped.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool until firm and cut.
Makes 5 pounds of fudge that never fails.

title: matzoh balls
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Then roll in balls. Put in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Keep cover on pot.
Do not re-cover.
Has to boil.
Great in soup.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Melt the chocolate and margarine in saucepan.
Combine the peanut butter, eggs and vanilla extract in a large bowl.
Beat in the melted chocolate mix.
Sift together the remaining ingredients into the peanut butter mix; mix well.
Spread in an 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 2 inch square pieces while hot.
Yield:
16 pieces.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt; add cooking oil, cold water, vanilla and vinegar.
Mix by hand (not with a mixer).
Do not beat too hard to have a good cake.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan at 325° for 45 minutes, or until it starts drawing away from the edge of pan.
Serve with your favorite icing.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Brown oxtails in oil after dredging in seasoned flour.
Reserve in same soup pot.
Saute carrots, celery, onion and garlic in frypan; reserve.
Add water, salt and peppercorns to soup pot. Simmer for 4 1/2 hours.
Add sauteed vegetables, tomato puree, barley and herbs.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add wine and correct seasoning and serve.

title: macaroni-cheese salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend salad dressing and mustard.
Toss lightly.

title: possum and potatoes
directions: Scrape, skin, clean and scald in boiling water the possum. Salt and pepper inside and out to taste.
Make a mixture of the bread crumbs, applesauce and chestnuts; stuff the mixture inside the possum.
Cover with sweet potatoes, 1 cup of water and lemon juice.
Bake in butter and baste often.
Bake until tender, about 2 hours.

title: old-fashioned orange ice cream
directions: In top of double boiler, over simmering water, combine milk, sugar and eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickens and coats back of spoon.
Cool, stir in cream and orange juice concentrate.
Transfer to ice cream freezer.
Freeze to instructions of manufacturer.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: chicken and cheese lasagna
directions: Heat butter in 2-quart saucepan over low heat; add garlic. Stir in flour and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in milk and broth.
Heat to boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in Mozzarella, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, the onion, basil, oregano and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until Mozzarella cheese is melted.
Spread 1/4 of the cheese sauce (about 1 1/2 cups) in a pan that has been sprayed with Pam, 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular; top with 3 or 4 uncooked noodles.
Spread half of the cottage cheese over the noodles.
Repeat with 1/4 of the cheese sauce, top with chicken and spinach, 1/4 of the cheese sauce, the remaining noodles and the remaining cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and garlic salt together in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, 8 3/4 x 13 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch, or 2 (8 x 8-inch) square Pyrex dishes.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili-egg puff
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon-colored.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and butter.
Stir in chilies.

title: orange-coconut cake
directions: Beat the butter and sugar to a cream; add the egg yolks and water, then the juice and rind of the orange; next, the flour, salt and baking powder sifted together, and fold in very gently the stiffly-beaten whites of the eggs.
Bake twenty minutes in a hot oven in layer-cake pans, and put the layers together with orange and coconut filling.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cut up potatoes, carrots, celery and onion.
Cover with water; boil until tender.
Drain; save water.
Pour melted cheese over the vegetables.
Add Pet milk, soup and water saved; stir and add corn.
Cook slowly for approximately 30 minutes.
Add mustard, salt and pepper.
Be careful; the soup will scorch if not careful. If too thick, add a little plain milk.

title: stuffed tomato appetizers
directions: Early in day, thinly slice tops from cherry tomatoes.
Remove pulp; drain shells upside down on paper towels.
Combine ham, horseradish and sour cream in small bowl.
Fill tomatoes; refrigerate.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes about 20 appetizers.

title: poor man's lobster 3
directions: Add fish seasonings and bay leaf to enough water to cover fish. Bring to a boil.
Put a chunk of butter into the water. Add fish and a bit of chopped onion and celery.
Lower heat and simmer 5 to 8 minutes or less. Test fish as they get done fast.
Serve with warm butter.

title: turkey fruit salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, honey and ginger.
Mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients except pecans.
Mix lightly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.
Stir in pecans just before serving.
This is a heavenly salad.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well. Add in carrots and nuts.
Put in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cube meat.
Brown in oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients except rice.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: jalapeno quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Place grated cheese in pie shells.
Pour mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cakes per directions; cool.
Start a layer of cake crumbled in a punch bowl, then cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple, vanilla pudding (made per directions), Cool Whip and pecan chips.
Do this layering until all used up.
Top with cherries and nuts.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.

title: easy fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.
In medium saucepan, combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, semi-sweet chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute, or until marshmallows melt completely.
Pour into pan; cool and cut into squares.
For thicker fudge, use a 7 x 5-inch pan.

title: amnor pancakes
directions: Combine buttermilk, yolks and shortening. Sift together dry ingredients; add to buttermilk mixture.
Stir until blended.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a loaf pan, melt butter, then pour out.
Save remaining butter after thoroughly greasing pan sides. In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, beer and sugar.
Pour batter into loaf pan.
Pour remaining butter over batter.
Bake 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Form into individual serving patties.
Fry until crispy and golden brown. Tasty, no one ever guesses it's zucchini.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes and 1/4 cup margarine well and pour into greased casserole.
Cover with crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup, onions and cheese.
Add vegetables, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
(Sometimes I add or substitute broccoli and/or cauliflower or corn or English peas.
I just use whatever I have.)
Pour into casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs that have been mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: scallop fritters
directions: Defrost scallops if frozen and dice.
Simmer 5 minutes in water to cover.
Drain and save 1/2 cup broth.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add to diced scallops with broth and eggs; mix well.
Drop by tablespoons into a little hot vegetable oil.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on absorbent paper. Makes about 18.
Serve with canned tomato mushroom sauce heated to serving temperature.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine next 7 ingredients and spread over top.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix together crackers, margarine and chopped nuts.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan (save 1/2 mixture for top of cake).
In mixing bowl, combine vanilla pudding and milk.
Mix and stir, then mix in ice cream.
Place on top of crumb mixture and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Add 1 (9 ounce) Cool Whip to top. (Will not need all Cool Whip.) Last sprinkle crumbs, that were saved, over top.
Try making the day ahead.
This is a great summer dessert.

title: easy corn bake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 1-1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add oil and blend.
Add eggs and beat.
Fold in carrots well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jackie's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to box directions, being careful not to overcook.
Chop the eggs, olives, celery, green pepper, radishes and onion.
Add chopped vegetables to cooked macaroni and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients and parsley according to your taste.
Refrigerate.

title: bird in bush
directions: Mix sausage and egg until well blended; divide into 8 even portions.
Roll hard-cooked eggs in flour to lightly coat.
Pat 1 portion of sausage around each egg to form thin, even coating. Roll eggs in bread crumbs to coat.
Heat oil to 375° over medium heat.
Fry 5 to 6 minutes until golden, turning often to brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Mix until creamy, roll out on waxed paper, spread with peanut butter.
Roll up, jelly roll style.
Slice and let dry.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Stir, mixing well.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Heat olive oil in large saucepan.
Add onion and saute until transparent.
Add basil, oregano and dill, heat through.
Add tomatoes.
Cook until soft, approximately 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and puree in blender or food processor.
Return contents to pan with chicken stock and heat for another 30 minutes.
Taste for seasoning and add pinch of sugar, if necessary.
May be served hot or cold.
If cold, garnish with dollop of nonfat yogurt.

title: grandpa's pie dough(grandpa liked only 2 kinds of pie: (1) hot pie, (2) cold pie.)
directions: Put dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg to measuring cup.
Add water to scant 1 cup.
Can roll out pie dough or press in pan.
Makes several pies.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, drain.
Rinse.
Add butter and cool.
Cook peas until done; cool.
Add cooled peas to macaroni. Stir in dressing.

title: cheddar veggie soup
directions: In a large pot, melt butter.
Add onions and celery; cook for about 10 minutes under medium heat.
Add carrots, broccoli and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add milk and Cheddar cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add cornstarch to thicken, if necessary.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: mandarin pork or chicken
directions: Mix water, Karo syrup, red pepper and corn starch until smooth. Stir in soy sauce. Set aside. In a large skillet heat 2 Tbsp. oil over high heat. Add meat and garlic. Stir for 5 minutes. Remove from skillet; drain off liquid. Heat 2 Tbsp. oil; add broccoli, onions and carrots. Stir for 2 to 3 minutes until crisp (or tender, depending on how you like it). Return meat to skillet. Stir in Karo syrup sauce mix. Bring to boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute. Serve over rice.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/4 cup gravy, bread cubes, onion, egg and salt. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Press into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and a meat thermometer reads 160°. Remove loaf from pan; drain on paper towels. Place on a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
